Six pound weight loss in three weeks, nausea continues. 28 Apr  Start Dose Pak with good results, follow directions by taking 6 pills first day, 5 pills second, etc. 4 May  No longer taking steroids and both knees are returning to former painful/inflammatory state.  Walking in difficult two more pounds lost due to nausea. Pain returning to previous levels, no improvement.  Being referred to a rheumatologist.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pfizer COVID-19 Vaccine EUA Patient received dose #1 of Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine on 3/6/2021 and Dose #2 on 4/24/2021.  Patient was found down on 4/25/2021 for an unknown amount of time and EMS was called. Patient noted to be seizing on EMS arrival. Blood glucose was noted to be 32 and an amp of D50 was administered. Patient arrested, received CPR (approximately 1 round) and was intubated in the field. His second glucose reading was undetectable and he received a second amp of D50. Patient also received sodium bicarb, calcium, and epinephrine and transported to ED. Patient subsequently transferred to Medical Center. He was treated for septic shock. His mentation remained very poor after pressors weaned off and sedation stopped. He likely had severe brain injury from hypoglycemia and anoxia - poor brainstem reflexed but did have spontaneous breathing - very poor prognosis - patient was extubated for comfort measures and all interventions stopped after family discussion and per their plan.
OTHER_MEDS: Amlodipine 10 mg BID, Calcitriol 0.5 mcg QD, (continued)arvedilol 12.5 mg BID, Ferrous sulfate 325 mg QD, Gabapentin 100 mg QD, Lisinopril 40 mg QD, Nicotine 7 mg Patch QD, Vitamin D2 50,000 units Weekly, Citalopram 20 mg QD, Flonase 2 spra

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around April 11, 2021, 15 days after my second Moderna vaccination, I began experiencing tingling in the fingers on my left hand and a tightening sensation around my left bicep. The sensations worsened the morning of April 13th and I was told by my primary doctor?s office to go to the ER. The ER doctors ordered bloodwork, EKGs and I think a CT scan. They ruled out heart attack or issues related to the heart and sent me home. Symptoms remained about the same for the following week. On the morning of April 22nd, the symptoms worsened. The tightening sensations in my left bicep and tingling in my fingertips became stronger. Then I began to experience pain in my bicep that moved up to my shoulder/clavical area. I went to my primary doctor?s office. The NP thought that it was most likely related to a pinched nerve and ordered an x-ray of my neck. The x-ray showed some slight compression of the vertebra in the neck. My husband requested that I be checked for a blood clot. The NP ordered an ultrasound and I returned later that day to have it done. A blood clot was found in the subclavian vessel on the left shoulder/clavical area. I was immediately given Eliquis. Symptoms worsen over the weekend. I returned to the ER on April 24th. They ran more bloodwork, EKGs and a CT scan of my head and chest since I was feeling like I couldn?t breathe and had a bad headache. They were unable to compare the size and location of the clot to Ultrasound from the doctor?s office. The prescribed anxiety medicines. I returned to my primary doctor?s office on May 3, 2021, for a follow up appointment. They ran more bloodwork to check for COVID antigens and clotting factors and x-rayed my pelvic area since I have been experiencing significant pain in my tailbone. They have also ordered a CT scan of my lower abdomen to rule out other possible causes of the clot. I?m waiting to hear the results of the bloodwork and for the CT appointment to be scheduled.
LAB_DATA: 4-13-21:  ER - Bloodwork, EKGs & CT scan (I think) 4-22-21:  X-ray of neck & Ultrasound 4-24-21:  ER - Bloodwork, EKGs & CT scan 5-3-21: Bloodwork, X-ray of pelvic area & ordered a CT scan
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin C, D & E Multi-vitamin Cyclobenzaprine Ibuprofen  Famotidine
HISTORY: Back pain from spinal fusion surgery (July 2020)

About a week after I took my Covid vaccine I started having, what I can only describe as minor uneasiness attacks triggered by random eveyday things and some claustrophobic feelings ? I could open a drawer and it would be dark and that would trigger this minor panic, I was able to close the drawer and think of something else and be just fine. Similar things, triggered by different mundane things kept happening. Then on May 2nd at night I was talking and a similar event triggered what I can only describe as a full blown panic attack. I was lying down and I had to immediately stand up, my mind was full of panic. One thought lead to another and the panic was growing. I have never experienced anything like this before. I had to start walking could not even stand still. Probably a few seconds in I started to do breathing exercises to start to calm myself down. It would work for a few seconds and the panic would creep back in. For what felt like the next 1-2 hours I kept using breathing and meditation techniques to get my mind in control and them was finally able to sleep. Today is May 4 and although the intensity is less I am still experiencing periodic ?panic attacks?. I can look at something mundane and that can trigger the ? I don?t know what to call it - ?anxiety?, Panic, unease and I have to start focusing on something else. There have been periods where I have felt better and almost back to normal and then it triggers again. I do not have a history of any such feeling nor do I ever remember feeling this way. I have never had an event where my mind was not stable, never had it be this disturb ever in my life. I do not believe there have been any other events that may describe this. The vaccine seems like the only change. I have been taking polyethylene glycol 3350 for probably many months, I don?t know if this interacts with the polyethylene glycol in the vaccine. I read that it can cause such neurological issues in children or prolonged use of it can cause loss of minerals which can cause similar issues. I don?t know if the combination of it with the vaccine did anything to exacerbate its effects? My doctor does not seem to think so. He seems to think the power has no such side effects. He says it is possible for the vaccine to cause such symptoms but he cannot be sure. He wrote me a prescription for Paroxetine 10mg ? I am afraid if chemical prescriptions/vaccines have caused this, then if they will really fix it. If I get a full panic attack again I will take it. For now I am trying my breathing and meditation exercises to calm myself if this happens ? it is difficult. My doctor has advised that if this is because of the vaccine the second dose might amplify these issues and to delay the second dose by a week if possible. I am trying to do that. I have looked at forum posts on websites detailing the general sideeffects and in the comments other people have listed similar experiences with anxiety attacks. If you search covid vaccine or Pfizer vaccine and panic attacks or anxiety you will find them. I am submitting this so that you are aware of this experience and can look at it if warranted. That experience was very difficult to get through and if it is caused by the vaccine it has to be addressed. If there is something to find and fix I wish you are able to do that. I apologize if this wasn?t described in the best way but I tried my best. Feel free to email me if you want more information.
LAB_DATA: My doctor has not ordered any
OTHER_MEDS: Metformin 1000mg (1 or 2 times a day) Glyxambi 10MG/5MG (1 time a day) Polyethylene Glycol 3350 17g (1 time a day - taking for an extended period - few months at least)
ALLERGIES: None that I am aware of

Patient says his BP has never been above 128/84 and that he just had his annual physical two weeks prior and it was good. EMTs were called since symptoms kept coming back. BP was 170/100s. Was transported to Hospital. He said they did a "brain test" having him touch his nose w/his finger, slid heels down shins, etc. but no other testing was done." He was discharged to home around 3PM and was told "he had an anxiety attack". He said they never really asked him what happened. Later that evening at 9:30PM, symptoms returned and he had to lie down. He had "pressure in his head, ringing in ears, and couldn't get up." Wife called EMTs. His vision was blurry. BP 150/110 upon exertion (movement) and 138/103 at rest, Pulse btw 105-110. He refused going back to hospital since they did nothing the 1st time. On Friday, April 2nd, I received my first dose of the Moderna vaccine.  Within minutes, my heart started racing and I felt faint.  Thereafter, my hands and face got the sensation of tingling.  It felt like ice was running through my veins.  My heart stopped racing approximately fifteen or so minutes after it began.  The tingling sensation in my hands and face ended approximately one hour later.  I also noticed a strange taste in my mouth during this same timeframe.  Subsequently, I had the sensation of being dizzy and lightheaded.  Importantly, I have never reacted to a vaccine in this manner.  On Saturday, April 3rd, I woke up with symptoms that were to be expected.  My arm was very sore and I felt a little achy.  However, I continued to feel dizzy and lightheaded.    That evening and for the next week or so, my heart was beating rapidly, and my blood pressure was elevated.  I also had the continuous feeling of my skin crawling.  My hands and feet also seemed to be experiencing tremors and twitching.    On Sunday, April 4th, I woke up and noticed that my right eye seemed a little blurry as I read an article on my phone.  I assumed I must have slept on my eye wrong and did not pay it much attention.  I do not recall my eye being blurry for the rest of the day.  The following morning on Monday, April 5th, I woke up once again feeling dizzy and lightheaded.  As I walked to the restroom, I noticed that my right eye was blurry again.  This time it seemed to be more pronounced.  Moreover, when I closed my right eye, I could see hundreds of dots in different colors.  In addition to having blurry vision, my legs felt weak and nearly buckled as I walked.  I felt like I was intoxicated.  Upon returning to bed, my teeth began chattering and I felt like I was freezing.  I called my doctor?s office and spoke with a PA who recommended that I go to the ER.    While I checked in at the ER, I could not remember my ZIP code.  I felt like my brain was not running on all cylinders.  Upon explaining my symptomology to the ER doctor, she recommended that I have my blood drawn and that I get an MRI to rule out a stroke.  All test results came back normal.    On Wednesday, April 7th, I made an appointment with an allergist.  They tested me to see if I was allergic to Polyethylene Glycol (PEG) and Polysorbate 80.  For the skin scratch portion of the test, neither of the substances had much of a reaction on my skin.  I thought the Polysorbate 80 scratch had a little bit of redness to it, but it was negligible.  When the doctor injected Polysorbate 80 under my skin with a syringe, a welt formed.  I am not sure why, but PEG was not injected in the same manner.  As a result of the test, the allergist confirmed that I am allergic to Polysorbate 80.  He mentioned that there may be instances of cross reactivity to PEG for individuals that are allergic to Polysorbate 80.  He recommended that I not get the second Moderna dose unless it was administered in a controlled setting.    On Sunday April 11th, I noticed what felt like a hard vein in my abdominal fat.  It felt slightly tender to the touch.  I was fearful that it could be a clot.  On Tuesday, April 13th, I woke up and as a I stood in the shower, my foot was painful to stand on.  On top of my right foot near my ankle, I could visibly see red inflammation in a vein.  I massaged the vein and the redness and pain dissipated.  Being fearful that I did have blood clots, I scheduled an appointment with a PA at my doctor?s office that same day.  We discussed my ongoing dizziness, lightheadedness, and me being fearful of blood clots.  She had an EKG performed at the office and ordered a barrage of blood tests.  Everything continued to be normal.    On Sunday, April 18th, I again went to the ER, because the hard vein in my stomach became larger and more tender to the touch.  When I bent over, it felt like there was a lot of pressure emanating from the hard vein down to my groin.  Once again, blood was drawn and everything was normal.  I also had an ultrasound performed on the area that felt like a hard vein and the doctor concluded that it was most likely swollen lymph nodes.  I was diagnosed with lymphadenopathy.    On Monday, April 26th, I scheduled an appointment with my primary care doctor to discuss the ongoing dizziness, lightheadedness, and pain in my stomach and groin area.  He told me that he had seen other patients that were experiencing similar symptoms and that my immune system was possibly overreacting to the vaccine.  He told me the symptoms should go away in time.  He also ordered a new blood test to check for clots.  The D-Dimer test came back normal.    On Tuesday, April 27th, I experienced a painful genital herpes outbreak.  I normally get one every year.  I had just recovered from an infection in December of 2020.  This outbreak was more intense and for the first time I had nerve pain that wrapped around my hip and down my inner thigh.  As of a week later, the infection is almost gone.      Today is May 4th, and I am still experiencing dizziness and lightheadedness.  Some days are better than others and every time I get optimistic that my dizziness and lightheadedness is finally gone, it reappears.  Being an IT consultant business owner and an attorney, I need to think clearly for my profession.  The side effects from the Moderna vaccine have made it very difficult to function.  I would like to get fully vaccinated, but I am fearful of getting the second shot.  I do not want the vaccine to cause permanent neurological damage or worse.    Finally, I am sure your organization is aware, but there are many other people experiencing the same symptoms as me.
LAB_DATA: 4/5/21 - Went to ER for blood tests and MRI to rule out stroke.  Results normal. 4/7/21 - Allergist administered allergy tests for PEG and Polysorbate 80.  Tests revealed an allergy to Polysorbate 80. 4/13/21 - Doctor's office administered blood tests and an EKG to rule out blood clots and issues with my heart.  Results normal. 4/18/21 - Went to ER for blood tests and an ultrasound to rule out a blood clot in abdomen.  Diagnosed with lymphadenopathy. 4/26/21 - PCP ordered a D-Dimer test to rule out blood clots which could be causing ongoing pain in stomach / groin area and neurological issues.  Results normal.
ALLERGIES: Acyclovir, tree pollens, grass pollen, and dogs.

The patient is a 50 y.o. female who presents to the Emergency Department with 3 days of a low abdominal discomfort with nausea and vomiting just today.  She says that she had decreased oral intake today due to her other symptoms and she had a low blood sugar of 65 earlier today.  She did not take her evening Lantus because of this.  She had already taken her usual Metformin and glipizide. She denies any fevers, denies any diarrhea.  Her last bowel movement was this morning and normal.  Denies any blood in the stools.  Denies any significant cough or breathing difficulty. Denies urinary symptoms, dysuria, hematuria. She reports that she is also had about 2 weeks of a left arm pain that comes and goes, and it seems to radiate to her trapezius.  She says that when the pain comes she feels a lump in her left outer arm.  She did see her PCP for this and was started on diclofenac about 1 week ago.  She says that this does help some.
LAB_DATA: RE-EVALUATION & FINAL ASSESSMENT:  11:57 PM Today's work-up is overall reassuring.  No evidence of diverticulitis, enteritis.  Findings were discussed with the patient with a interpreter. I feel that she is appropriate for discharge at this time and the patient is comfortable with this plan. She will be given medications for HA and nausea. She has been provided with a prescription for Zofran.  I advised her that if she ends up having decreased p.o. intake over the next couple days secondary to this illness, then she should withhold her glipizide.  I advised her that the Metformin should not cause her to be hypoglycemic, and her Lantus is slow acting and it should not cause hypoglycemia either.  The glipizide would be the most concerning.  Advised her that if she eats as usual then she should take all of her medicines as usual.  She verbalized understanding.  The patient has also been advised to follow up with her PCP for further evaluation. Home care instructions and return precautions were discussed prior to discharge.

D/C summary from 4/26 : Patient is a 58 y.o. female patient of, DO with history of OSA cannot tolerate CPAP, depression, rheumatoid arthritis, chronic pain syndrome, obesity, diabetes type 2, CAD, hypertension, hyperlipidemia, TIA who presents with shortness of breath. Her CTPA and venous duplexes were negative for blood clots. There was bronchitis on CTPA so pt was placed on albuterol, mucinex and advised to use IS. Her Cr was elevated to 1.52 and improved to 1.25 this morning. Her hydrochlorothiazide was held. Her AST was 186, ALT 245 previously normal. Her atorvastatin and metformin were held. She was tolerating po and her VS were stable so she was discharged home. Patient received 2nd dose of Pfizer Covid-19 vaccine at 2:15 pm on April 30, 2021. Patient started having a reaction to the vaccine at 2:30 pm. She was given a 50 mg (20 ml)dose of  liquid Benadryl (12.5 mg/5 ml) at 2:32 pm followed by famotidine 20 mg tablet. Her throat was examined with a flashlight and it did not appear to be swollen. Her blood pressure (135/87 mmHg), pulse (65 bpm), and pulse ox (98%) were measured at 2:40 pm. Patient was timed for 5 minutes to see if symptoms improved her worsened and her symptoms improved. She was given water and monitored until 3 pm where she continually improved. The patient left at that time and followed back up with the pharmacist via text at 3:30 pm and was feeling normal. She patient had an Auvi-Q with her if her symptoms returned or worsened.

She feels that she lost about 80-85% of her hearing on the left side. She was told that she had fluid in her ear - to go home take a decongestant and nasal spray. At 3 days, there was no improvement, so she went to her PCP. They examined her ear and did not see any fluid, but referred her to an ENT MD. As it would have taken more time to get in to see an ENT, she made an appointment with an audiologist. She saw the audiologist on 3/17/2021. Her hearing had returned by this time. The audiologist said she had seen several patients who had experienced hearing loss and about 50% had not had their hearing return. This client's hearing tested above average at this time.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I woke up feeling like someone punched me hard in the arm, my entire arm hurt from the shoulder to my elbow and was even worse to the touch.  The next day I started running a fever and slept most of the day.  By day 2 I had a headache only.

18 hours after the 2nd Covid19 Pfizer vaccine, I began to feel lightheaded with a headache. 15 minutes later I became extremely fatigued and felt like I was going to pass out. I stumbled down the hallway to a family member for help and collapsed. I could not stand or walk and could barely talk. The family member helped me to a vehicle and drove me to urgent care. I had to be taken inside by wheelchair as I could not walk, could barely move. At the urgent care facility they took my vitals and all were normal. Oxygen at 100%, BP  was a bit high. They said this was a "normal" reaction to the Covid 19 vaccine. I had read about extreme fatigue....but not to the point of not being able to even stand up. I was sent home and slept almost non-stop for the next 48 hours. The fatigue lasted another 4 days after that.
Gave vaccination outside of recommended time interval was only 3 weeks instead of 2 months

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1st Shingrix shot on 11-25-2019 - no adverse reaction.  2nd Shingrix shot on 2-18-2021.   Late in the evening of 2-21-21, left eye was scratchy & irritated.  Condition worsened by morning with redness and a crusty discharge.   Went to Urgent Care morning of 2-22-21.  Initial diagnosis was possible bacterial infection. Rx for Ciprofloxacin.  No improvement so returned to Urgent Care 2-24-21.  Slit-lamp exam revealed dendritic lesion on cornea - diagnosis of dendritic keratitis. Referred to ophthalmologist. Saw ophthalmologist afternoon of 2-24-21.  Image taken of anterior segment. Assessment:  Dendritic keratitis of left eye due to herpes simplex virus.  Artificial tears recommended. RX for valACYclovier HCl-1 - 1 gm oral tablet. RX for Zirgan 0.l1% ophthalmic gel was not approved by insurance company.  Rx for Trifluridine added several days later.  Follow-ups with ophthalmologist on 2-26-21 and 3-3-21.  Advised lesion was gone and no scar tissue was visible.  Condition slowly improved over the next week but irritation upon awakening continued for an additional week or so.  The event was extremely stressful as I feared I would suffer with permanent scar tissue resulting in impaired vision.  NOTE:  I had shingles under my eye (thought it was under my right eye, but one of the ophthalmologists said it was likely under my left eye) when I was between 11-14 years old.  PCP does not think the dendritic keratitis was a reaction to the Shingrix vaccine but the timing is very suspect.
OTHER_MEDS: B-Complex Oral Capsule Cal-Citrate Plus Vitamin D TABS Estradiol 0.1 MG/GM Vaginal Cream
HISTORY: Lumbar and Thoracic back pain. Rhomboid and/or trapezius pain. Periodic cold sores (herpes simplex) on lip.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: She got her vaccine, and felt weak and disoriented to begin with and broke out into a sweat and does not remember much after that.  Vaguely remembered somebody asking her if she was okay.  She was sat down and felt like she was coming back.  She does not remember anything for the next 32 hours.  She vaguely remembers being in the car, knows that she was seeing double cars in front of her, felt like she was in a dream.  The traffic lights were like a film.  Her daughter said that she saw her in Knoxville which was 35 minutes from where she was supposed to be.  Then had a doctors appointment and was told that she was not her.  It then took her 4 hours to get home, which is normally a 45 minute drive.  She does not remember where she had gone.  She was very shaky inside and got home and went to bed.  She is still having that shaky inside feeling.  She went to bed and did not get up until Friday night when her grandchildren came to the house.  She got up and could not remember them being there and them playing, does not remember them leaving, and does not remember locking up her house.  She met her daughter on Saturday and told her what was going on and she told her to go back home.  She was shaky with her hands and spilled everything.  She cannot remember anything, and not able to tell distances.  She can remember of different times of slamming on her breaks and almost hitting things.  The drug store called and nobody knew where she was for the 32 hour period of time.  This fogginess is kind of going away now, but still has the real shaking inside like she's had too much caffeine.  She called her doctor and left a message for them to call her back.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3rd morning after 2nd shot (5-1-21),I  developed sharp pain from nerve compression in lower spine while sitting. No reason has been determined for this happening. I went to urgent care and the doctor said it was a compressed spinal nerve with inflammation. He gave me a shot of an NSAID near the spine and put me on a 5 day course of Prednisone. He also prescribed pain killers and muscle relaxant to use as needed.
LAB_DATA: (5-3-21) The doctor did in-office physical movement tests and confirmed I had almost no muscle control over my left leg. He said this indicated a spine and nerve issue. He did not order a scan to determine the exact cause as he said the initial course of treatment would be the same no matter what. There was no incident determined that would caused this sudden inflammation. The doctor said if didn't heal with the steroids or if it got worse, the next step would be to order a scan. As of the day after, I'm still in pain but there is some improvement.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was hospitalized 2Xs immediately after receiving the 2nd Covid-19 vaccination for coronary artery blockages: 3/19 and again 3/22. I had been experiencing what I thought was heartburn and was referred to by PCP to a cardiologist who ordered a stress test that I passed. After suffering severe pain in my sternum from 11:00 pm 3/18-1:00 am 3/19 I went to the hospital. An EKG showed no coronary issues yet at 7 am I was taken to the cardiac catheter lab where it was discovered i had a 100% blockage. A stent was implanted and i was released around 4:30 pm the afternoon of 3/20. The morning of 3/22 I once again experienced severe chest pain and called an ambulance. I was told by the EMT my heart rate reached more than 200. I was rushed back to the same hospital where a 2nd cardiac catheter was performed. It was discovered that the stent implanted 48 hours earlier had a 100% blockage. It was opened and several additional stents were implanted. I was kept in the ICU for 2 days for observation and then released. No one I've spoken with since can verify what caused the 2nd episode. Several people at the hospital speculated the cause for the 2nd attack may have been a single dose of Brilinta that had been missed Saturday evening because by the time my wife got me home from the hospital and settled our pharmacy was closed. She picked up my prescriptions first thing Sunday morning and I took everything as directed. My cardiologist agreed with  me that missing 1 dose should not have caused such an adverse reaction.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Heart felt like it was pounding out of my chest on Monday evening on April 26, 2012. I spent 24 hours in the ICU, and another 24 hours in Cardiac Care.  I was released on Friday, April 30 at around 2:30 pm.  I am now prescribed Eliquis, have a follow up with my PCP on Monday, , May 10, a follow up with cardiology on May 24, and a follow up on June 14 with the Pulmonary Embolism group.

Patient received first dose of Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. Patient's husband alerted staff that patient was feeling lightheaded. When provider approached pt she was unresponsive, spastic with obstructed breathing and diaphoretic. Patient lowered to floor supine with knees elevated and regained consciousness after a total of roughly 45 seconds. Patient was not oriented to place. Patient became unconscious again for roughly 15 seconds and became alert with the use of smelling salts. Patient and husband endorsed history of syncopal episodes with prior vaccines. Patient endorsed anxiety surrounding vaccine administration. Patient denied any medical history aside from anxiety and specifically denied neuro history of seizures or pseudo-seizures. EMS was called immediately upon finding patient spastic with obstructed breathing. Patients pulse and O2 saturation were within normal limits for the entire episode. Her blood pressure was low with a systolic in the 90s initially, but increased to roughly 115 prior to EMS arrival. Patient remained alert and oriented x3. She was evaluated by EMS and taken to the hospital for further workup for possible seizure activity.

First pregnancy - EDC 09/18/21, RH negative (spouse is positive), Advanced maternal age  - First adverse event on 09/11/21 included minor spotting while using the bathroom 2 days after 2nd dose of the Pfizer shot - pregnancy at 17 weeks, 1 day. I contacted my doctor via the online message system and advised her of the spotting. She instructed me to rest and take fluids.  - Second adverse event on 09/13/21 (17 weeks, 3 days pregnant)- I woke up with a swollen right eye, which was crusted shut with mucus. My first thought was that it was either debris in my eye or pink eye. I made an appointment with the eye doctor and he said that it's likely a stye forming and to use a warm compress.  - Third adverse event on 09/16/21 (17 weeks, 6 days pregnant) - I tried using the bathroom to pass a stool and was finding myself a bit constipated (which hasn't been uncommon in this pregnancy). I experienced enough bleeding to have blood in the toilet and continuous blood while wiping. I went immediately to the ER for treatment.
LAB_DATA: First event: Spoke with my doctor via the online message portal (04/12/21). No further treatment required.  Second event: Went to the eye doctor to have my eye looked at (and inspected for debris) on 04/13/21. Used a warm compress on the subject eye throughout the day. No further treatment required.  Third event: Went to the ER for treatment/observation. ER took blood tests and urine sample to check on pregnancy and levels. Received a detailed ultrasound checking on the baby, placenta and cervix - no problems found. Baby appeared healthy. Admitted to an ER room and the doctor issued saline via IV, performed a pelvic exam and confirmed bleeding was vaginal (not from the anus). Doctor determined I had a minor bladder infection and some inflammation/irritation of the cervix, however, the bleeding had since stopped. I was administered the Rhogam shot (to prevent my blood from developing antibodies against the baby or future pregnancies, due to my rh negative blood type) and prescribed 5 days of Keflex (4 times daily) for the bladder infection. I was discharged approximately 5 hours later with instructions to follow up with my PCP. I saw my PCP on 04/21/21 ? baby and me are healthy. No explanation for the bleeding found other than ?it can be normal for some mothers?.
OTHER_MEDS: Daily Pre-Natal Vitamin 1/2 dose of Unisom once nightly for insomnia Daily probiotic supplement

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 25-year-old male with past medical history of depression with anxiety, esophagitis and hemorrhoids.  Patient presented with petechial rashes all throughout his body  started on Friday 4/9 after getting a tattoo the day prior and his first moderna covid vaccine 3/28.  On admission patient was found to have a platelet count of 1. Heme/ onc was consulted and thrombocytopenia was deemed secondary to ITP.  Hepatitis B panel, showed previous hepatitis B infection, although results may be inaccurate due to patient receiving IVIG prior to hepatitis panel being done.  Patient also had an equivocal syphilis result, which also could be a false positive due to immune response.  Patient received 2 IVIG, 4 days of Decadron, and 1 dose of Nplate.  Patient did not receive rituximab, due to stable increasing platelet count.  Patient received hepatitis-B prophylaxis for 2 days in case he were to receive rituximab.  Platelet count now stable at 25, to follow-up with hematology in 1 week outpatient for repeat CBC.  Patient also to follow-up with his Primary Care Physician in 1 week.
CUR_ILL: depression with anxiety, esophagitis and hemorrhoids

32 year old female lost consciousness approximately 5 minutes after receiving her first dose of Pfizer vaccine.  Patient was found to be unresponsive to verbal or painful stimuli, pale and diaphoretic.  Patient was immediately placed supine on a cot at vital signs obtained with EMS activated.  All vital signs stable and patient regained consciousness but was slow to respond to questions.  Patient denied any other complaints.  No chest pain, SOB, weakness, dizziness, blurred vision, tinnitus, and no signs of anaphylaxis or stroke.  Patient became A & O x4 and continued to deny any other complaint.  Negative medical history, allergies or medications.  Last oral intake was breakfast this morning and she denied any alcohol or drug use.  EMS arrived on scene and assumed patient care.  All risks and consequences up to and including death were explained but patient signed AMA and eft with her husband via private vehicle.

Within a few minutes (5-10 minutes post vaccination) of sitting down in the observation area I felt a burning sensation to the right and slightly above the vaccination site. This was followed by random areas on the right arm having numbness, pins and needles, and burning. From the right side the sensations continued to other parts of the body (eyelids, arms, feet, chest, scalp etc). Not a single area of the body is untouched except for maybe the toungue. The areas are roughly 1 cm- a couple of inches in diameter and there is no observable pattern to the areas that feel the sensations. Some of them are pretty painful. The sensations have reduced over days but have not gone away. I am not able to sleep well as a result of having these jolts which feel almost like an electric shock.

She had gone to the doctor as she was having issues with hives.  The doctor asked her if she had the Shingles vaccine, and she told her no and she administered the vaccine without permission that she is aware of.  She told her that she did not want the vaccine, and that she was there for treatment of the hives and she thought she was getting a steroid shot to help her with her present symptoms.  She feels now that she was some sort of experiment now.    She got the vaccine and within 2 weeks she started having  loosing her hair to the point that she lost it all, it's now about 1" long.  She had not cut her hair in over 4 years.  She started getting blisters all of her body and her body started turning red.  She lost all her nails on her hands and her feet, very very painful.  She couldn't touch anything, could not walk to the bathroom and had to get a bedside commode and for 3 months she had to wear diapers as she did not have the strength to get out of bed.  She is down to 176# right now ,but weighed 210# at the time of the vaccine.   She has to moisturize her skin every 2-3 hours as she had scales and the dryness was so bad that her skin was cracking and she could see her under skin.  She could not shower as the pressure of the water felt like she was being cut in half.   She went back to the doctor at that time and she refused to help her and told her that the vaccine could not have done that to her, but she had not had any reaction like that before the vaccine.     She has had skin problems her entire life but never had a reaction like this until the vaccine.    She would have to fill the tub with more cold than hot and used aloe vera shampoo and body wash mixed and sit in it and try to run water over her body and it would cause her skin to fall off.   She would have to shower with the lowest setting, and then moisturize again.  She could not bear the feeling of the wind on her skin as it would start to scale and had to have a blanket at all times due to chills.  She still gets blisters a little but moisturizes to make sure that it stays under control.   She is in a lot of pain due to this reaction.  She has gotten to a new doctor who is treating her with Benadryl and steroids, which finally after 5 months has started to help her and improve.    Her skin continued to scale off and if she does not moisturize for 6 hours then she will start to react the same way.    Due to this she has lost her job, which she worked her entire life, and was evicted from her home due to not able to pay rent due to loss of income.  They increased in November without any notice, no repairs to her apartment, no heat or central air, never late on her rent, but the apartments were under new management and increased the rent $300.00 more.
HISTORY: Asthma reaction to vaccines, gets flu with flu vaccine.
PRIOR_VAX: Flu vaccine 6-8 years ago, ended up in the hospital due to flu-like symptoms and breathing difficulties.

Patient received the 1st COVID vaccine (Pfizer, Lot #: EW0161 and expiration date: 08/2021) on 04/13/2021 at 10:57 AM. Client presented to the vaccine site today, 05/04/2021, for her second dose appointment. As the vaccinator conducted a health screening, some medical concerns came up. As a result, nurse was called over to consult. Client expressed that while she was waiting in the observation area after her first dose, she developed lower jaw discomfort within 15 minutes of receiving the vaccine and it lasted for a total of 30 minutes. Client reported that the discomfort was rated as a 3 out of 10 on a pain scale and since it resolved, it has not come back. Client also reported that the following day, she developed a rash around the injection site. The rash lasted about a week and the client described it as being itchy and that it would exacerbate about 2- 3 times a day. The rash has since resolved, but there is still a slight, bruise- like area at the injection site. Client denied any past medical history and denied any current medical diagnoses. Client is not currently taking any medications and has anaphylactic reactions to Penicillin, IV contrast, Prednisone, and anesthesia. The client reports having a primary care provider, but stated that she did not consult with the provider regarding the symptoms experienced after receiving the first dose. Nurse requested a medical consult and the medical doctors recommended that a set of vital signs be taken. If the vital signs came back within normal ranges, we could proceed. The client would receive the second dose and then wait in the observation area for 30 minutes. Vital signs were taken by medic, at 1224, while the client was sitting: blood pressure: 128/80, heart rate: 76, respiratory rate: 14, and skin was warm, dry, intact, and normal. Vital signs were stable, so patient received the 2nd COVID vaccine (Pfizer, Lot #: EW0167 and expiration date: 08/2021) on 05/04/2021 at 12:21 PM. Client was educated to follow up with her primary care if the lower jaw discomfort and rash developed after the second dose. Client then checked in with the EMT and was educated on the use of V- safe. Client sat in the observation area and waited a total of 30 minutes. Client then left the vaccine site with a steady gate.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a pleasant 63-year-old gentleman who came to the hospital originally on 4/10/2021, refer you to the H&P done at that time by Dr. Comes in with a diffuse rash over his torso and his legs. He did get COVID vaccine, his first one (4/1/21 at Imaginetics) about a week to a week and a half before admission. He said shortly thereafter is when his symptoms began. The rash is pruritic. He had no breathing troubles whatsoever. No throat closing or tongue swelling, etc. No mouth lesions and in fact the rash over his torso and his back is pretty minimal, looks more like a sunburn type appearance. In any case, also had a petechial type of purpuric rash on his legs and I did show this to Dermatology who felt that it did look like vasculitis. He was placed on                                                                                                                                                                                                                      steroids. He did SOLU-MEDROL while here and this was converted to prednisone on discharge for which he will continue with for the next few weeks. Slow taper. Rash had improved over his stay here. His LFTs were also up somewhat as well, but these did improve while he was here and multiple imaging studies were done including ultrasound, CAT scan and abdominal Doppler all were negative for any kind of                                                        pathology. Suspect probably these elevated LFTs could have been from vasculitis and that is also improving now with the steroids. He is tolerating diet well. He has no abdominal pain. Okay to be discharged today.  We will continue with prednisone taper. Follow with PCP in 1 week. Also know, there is an ANA pending as further workup for                                                                                                                                                            vasculitis. We will defer to PCP on follow up for that.    4/21/21                                                                                                                                                       Follow-up with PCP: 63-year-old male here for a hospital follow-up. He was hospitalized for rash suspected to be vasculitis and elevated LFTs-started 2-3 days after his COVID vaccine. Etiology of elevated LFTs unclear. Liver US and CT were negative. Hepatitis, viral testing, and ANA negative. Received his first COVID vaccine on 4/1. Still on prednisone taper for rash. He is feeling better, still somewhat tired. Rash is almost resolved. Current complaints sore on the left side of his tongue for the past 11 days. Initially hurt when he would eat, is better now. Is back at work. Denies abdominal pain nausea, vomiting, stool changes, dark or light stools, yellowing of skin, swelling in abdomen or legs. Does not use tobacco, alcohol, or drugs. No history of liver issues. Normal LFTs 7 months ago. Follow up appt at Allergy/Immunology on 4/29/21: Plan: Patient had a delayed reaction to his 1st dose of Pfizer vaccination that included symptoms of arthralgias, rash as well as elevated liver enzymes.  His symptoms don't meet criteria for type 1 IgE mediated reaction so skin testing would not be beneficial.  His symptoms required hospitalization and improved with tapered steroid course.  His symptoms did not fit DRESS syndrome criteria as he did not have peripheral eosinophilia, fevers, sloughing of skin/oral mucosa or blistering.  We discussed how there is not much data or case reports about how to proceed with completing vaccination for COVID.  I would recommend he get Johnson & Johnson vaccination since it is a different class of vaccine and he may not have the same reaction but again this is not guaranteed.  There is a small chance of clotting with Johnson & Johnson vaccine as well.  He should pre-medicate with cetirizine 20 mg po qday for 1 week before vaccination and 2 weeks after.  I would also suggest he get a steroid course to have on hand from his PCP in case rash starts again after vaccination.  It may be beneficial to have him get lab work several days after vaccination as well (U/A, CBC, CMP) to evaluate for any inflammation.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 0n 4-23-21 I was going to sleep when my arms started burning then my legs, my face and upper chest. I had a rash, swelling and redness    that started in my arms to finally my head. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I don't know if this is known already as I've seen muscle/joint pain listed as a reaction but in addition to chills, aches, fever, I experienced continual, radiating bone pain in my hip and thigh area from about 11:30 am on 4/29/21 until the evening of 4/30/21. As of 5/4/21, I am again feeling pain in my hip/butt area. Tylenol or similar might resolve but I thought it was important to advise this information. My mother-in-law who had her vaccine weeks before me had the same, exact symptom. Sleeping was very helpful in not focusing on the pain. My mother-in-law had the same pain in the same area when she had the vaccine weeks before me.   On a positive note, I did notice that immediately after the 1st vaccine a rash developed on my neck sometime in January (which required me to stop wearing a gold necklace I always wore) went away immediately after the 1st dose of the vaccine. I had tried using several creams and tea tree oil long before the vaccine with little relief. Additionally, I am inclined to believe that when I got VERY sick if back in Feb. 2020 that I probably had Covid resulted in me having Pneumonia. It left me constantly having to clear my throat of mucus and it was so bad early on that I had to use an inhaler and a nebulizer from Feb 2020 until the 1st dose of the vaccine in 2021 when it started to improve. It has improved even more since the 2nd vaccine.
LAB_DATA: I did not seek medical attention for the bone pain but I did take acetaminophen and rest. I tried walking to see if that would help but it didn't seem to help or make it worse.
HISTORY: Osteoporosis, no not Osteopenia, yes Osteoporosis.

On 4/25/21, lost mucus plug in the AM at 17 weeks pregnant with no other issues, concerns, abnormalities, etc. At 3:50AM on 4/27/21, ruptured membrane/water broke. Induced at 11:20pm on the 27th and delivered at 5:30am on 4/28/21 at 17 weeks and 3 days a baby boy measuring 8.25 inches and 5.6 ounces.   No placental infection or abnormalities. Pathology noted an abruption hematoma that could have resulted from induced labor. No trauma, blood work, or other explanations for early rupture of what was a perfectly healthy and growing baby.

No infection or abnormalities of the placenta aside from acute abruption as noted above. Bloodwork from 10 weeks, 11 weeks, 15 weeks, and 17 weeks was all normal. Additional rule out bloodwork outstanding per patients request.

I received my second Pizer vaccine Tuesday, April 27 in the morning. My partner woke me up about 12:30 am Wednesday morning because I was thrashing about in bed. Shortly after waking up, I felt sick to my stomach and got out out bed to go to the bathroom thinking I needed to throw up. I stumbled to the bathroom and then collapsed on the floor. My arms and hands had gone numb. My legs were going numb. I couldn't stand. I couldn't move my fingers at all. They seemed locked in place. My partner could manipulate my fingers and I could feel his touch on my body, but my brain and body seemed unable to communicate correctly for me to move under my own control.  I thought I needed to go to the emergency room. My partner reminded me that it was the covid shot and convinced me to take Tylenol. I was concerned I couldn't swallow and I was unable to hold a cup, but my partner assisted me and I was able to take medication.  After a time (maybe 30 minutes), the numbness gave way to tingling and I was able to feel and move my body again. I was nauseous and oscillating between cold and hot. My partner helped me to stand and walk back to bed. While these initial symptoms left,  I remained feverish, nauseous, and fatigued from Wednesday until Sunday. Monday, May 3 was my first full day without any symptoms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day after receiving my first dose of the vaccine, my neuropathy symptoms worsened significantly from their prior state. I felt increased nerve pain, twitching, numbness/tingling, and a feeling of weakness in my arms and legs. These worsened symptoms have persisted as of the date of this submission.  Additionally, 10 days after the first dose of the vaccine, I also began experiencing significant dizziness, weakness and shakiness throughout my body.  I went to the ER twice for these persistent symptoms to rule out emergency conditions. The first and second ER visits were on April 23, 2021 and April 25, 2021, respectively.  The testing done during my ER visits (various bloodwork, urinalysis, EKGs, CT scan of head, MRI and MRV of brain) did not find a specific cause of these symptoms. I am currently in the process of following up with a cardiologist and neurologist after my recent ER visits, so the results of some additional tests are pending.  The testing done so far has not identified any other cause of these symptoms.  I never had any dizziness prior to the vaccine, and my neuropathy issue has definitely worsened after the vaccine. I continue to experience the aggravated neuropathy and dizziness as of the date of this submission.
OTHER_MEDS: Zyrtec for seasonal allergies (over the counter dose).
HISTORY: Existing idiopathic small fiber neuropathy (which, prior to the vaccine, was improving and primarily affecting only the right hand and right lower leg and foot) from suspected prior COVID infection in March 2020. I have been seeing neurologists for the past year who have ruled out other possible causes of the neuropathy.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin, doxycycline, clarithromycin, hazelnuts, and raw, pitted tree fruit.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 5/4/2021, client approached EMT complaining of discomfort. Client was a 47 year old female alert and tracking with her eyes. Client had a chief complaint of general malaise. For the duration of the assessment and history taking, an interpreter assisted with translation. Client stated that after 15 minutes of her observation, she began to experience malaise as well as generalized pain behind her eye and in her throat. This is the client's second dose of the pfizer vaccine (Lot #EW0167 Exp 08/2021) and she has a history of an allergy to cephalexin and reglan. Client denied any reactions to the first dose of the vaccine. Assessment revealed no swelling, hives, discoloration, shortness of breath or other signs of anaphylaxis throughout the patient's body. Client complained of malaise but denied wanting to faint. Client complained of pain behind her eye and in her throat but had no excessive salivation or difficulty speaking. Client stated that she only had orange juice for breakfast this morning. Client's initial vitals at 1025 were 120/80 blood pressure, 80 heart rate, respirations 16, lung sounds clear bilaterally, alert and oriented to person, place, date and event, temperature 98 f and her skin was warm and normal. EMT present was unable to obtain an O2 sat due to client's fingernail paint. Client stated that the symptoms she complained of today did not resemble her allergic reaction to IV antibiotics. Client consented to remaining an additional 30 minutes and her vitals were monitored at 5 minute intervals. Client was provided with a snack and water and had no difficulty eating or swallowing during her extended observation. Client's vitals remained stable throughout her additional observation period and were as follows: 1030 - 116/76, pulse 80, respirations 16, 1035 - 116/76 blood pressure, 80 pulse, 16 respirations, 1040 - 116/76, 80 pulse, 16 respirations, 1045 - 118/76 blood pressure, 80 pulse, respirations 16, 1050 - 114/74 blood pressure, 80 pulse, 16 respirations, 1055 - 114/74, 80 pulse, respirations 16. Client did state she had slightly more energy after eating a snack and drinking water. However, she continued to state that her eye pain and throat pain was still present. Client was asked if she needed staff present to dial 911 but client refused stating she wanted to "see how she feels." Client was offered 50 mg of Benadryl but refused stating she would "take some when she gets home." Client was encouraged to contact her primary or seek out urgent care today if symptoms do not improve. Client was provided with all relevant information regarding the vaccine and possible side effects. Client departed borderview at 1057 stating she felt safe to drive and stating that her husband will be with her when she gets home. Client remained a total of 45 minutes with no anaphylaxis reaction.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This is only a moderate adverse event, but I wanted to add it to the record in case more people have similar experiences. // Day 1 - mild pain at injection site, no other issues. Took Advil. // Day 2 - Flu-like body pains/sensitivity, very uncomfortable, foggy brain, spent most of the day in bed because that made it less uncomfortable. (I understand this is a typical 2nd shot reaction. No problems there.) Took Advil. // Day 3 - Felt fine when I woke, no more full body pains except continuing strong pain at injection site. Pain level totally managable. Continued the Advil. // Evening of Day 3 - Arm hurting a lot now. Migraine started,  back started cramping, neck cramped so badly it became nearly immobile. Pain in arm still pretty strong. Continued the Advil. // Day 4 - Pain continued, very slightly less. Continued the Advil. // Day 5 - Pain considerably less, arm pain very mild, back and neck cramping stopped completely. Residual soreness/stiffness, but that's it. Migraine gone.
HISTORY: Hashimoto's, (And Fibromyalgia symptoms that I've been managing for years -- but no official diagnosis for that one. My doctor had prescribed Lyrica years back but I eventually found other ways to manage the pain (exercise, activity restrictions, foods I avoid, etc). So I haven't had a major flare up of that for a while. Back in my mid thirties I was having flare ups every few weeks though.)

The patient is a 49 year old male who has a past medical history significant for bipolar disorder with manic episodes, OSA on CPAP, morbid obesity, HLD, and  relapsing remitting MS.  Per chart review, patient's MS was initially diagnosed in 2012 on MRI and LP and was on Copaxone for several years but stopped taking in 2017.  Symptoms and imaging remained stable through 2019 then patient was lost to follow up until he was seen by Dr.  on 4/12/21 who ordered an outpt MRI.   Patient had COVID vaccine with Jansen vaccine on 4/10/21.  He developed bilateral upper and lower exremity weakness and urinary retention on 4/21/21 which prompted presentation.  He came into ED 4/21/21 and had foley placed but removed foley and decided to leave AMA. Returned on 4/22/21 with worsening symptoms and was subsequently admitted. Patient was seen by neurology and started on high dose steroid x5d for MS exacerbation. Initial MRI of the brain obtained on 4/22/21 was notably stable without change in previously described white matter disease. No new lesions to suggest active demyelination. New plaques were noted on MRI C and T spine (4/22/21). It is noted that patient received COVID19 vaccination with J&J vaccine on 4/10/21 and temporal relationship between his acute presentation and recent vaccination was questioned.    On 4/30/21, patient developed severe bilateral facial weakness and he additionally was reported to have had an episode of aspiration.  Repeat MRI brain on 4/30/21 showed new bilateral facial nerve enhancement. Etiologies could include: GBS, Lyme disease, botulism, neurosarcoidosis, less likely myasthenia gravis.  LP was pursued on 5/1/21 which was significant for tube 4 with 136 WBC, 88% lymphocytes, glucose 89, protein 632. Meningitis/encephalitis panel was negative.  Lyme CSF was negative, Lyme antibody panel was positive.  MuSK antibody negative.  ACE blood level normal.  Ganglioside antibody panel and myasthenia graivs adult panel pending. He is being treated for Lyme disease with Ceftriaxone 2g IV daily since 5/1/21 with plan for 2-4 week course to cover for Lyme disease.  He is still admitted and is still having symptoms of facial palsy as of today (5/4/21)

Note that after shot number 1 , I had nothing more than a sore arm, but I did get the raised welt 'Covid Arm' about a week after. No pain after day 1.  After shot #2 on May 1, the arm has been minimally sore. I felt totally normal for about 24 hours. After about 24 hours, however, I started to feel fatigued and brain-fogged. Then I developed muscle aches in the neck and shoulder area. Also got a low-grade fever (normal for me is 97.5 and when I checked it was 98.1). Taste was off during that time as well. I felt hungry but my stomach was queasy and nothing tasted right, so I didn't eat much. After 24 hours of that, where I slept a lot, I improved quickly.  Could almost feel stronger by the hour. Monday (day 2) I worked all day (on the computer) and struggled a little, but was mostly fine. After work, I did some work landscaping with digging and hard work and was fine. Then a day later I noticed the injection site in the left arm had a raised welt, but smaller and not discolored in the same way it was after the first shot. (After the first shot, the welt that showed up a week later was not colored in the middle but had a reddish but subtle ring around the injection site, I'd say about 3 inches in diameter.) I noticed small, red patches in a line surrounding the welt. Nothing painful, just interesting. Now, it looks more uniformly red and it is tiny bit tender, but nothing bad. Energy is back to 100%. Brain is working perfectly. I wanted to report my symptoms to help others and to fill in data.
PRIOR_VAX: Major arm pain/stiffness after high dose tetanus shot for like 3 weeks, but nothing more. June 2020.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After my J&J vaccine, I experienced fever, chills and a left sore arm and those symptoms resolved in 24 hours. On 04-06-2021 I experienced headaches on and off and on 04-07-2021, I had light headiness, an air-filled pressure sensation to my eyes, forehead, more like a sinus headache. On 04-14-2021, I went to see my PCP due to my headaches continuing, the doctor ran complete blood panel test were performed along with a D-dimmer test to rule out blood clots and he told me to take Advil as pain medication.  My D-dimmer test was normal. I noticed when bending down my headaches became worse. On 04-20-2021, an MRI of the brain was performed. On 05-01-2021, I experienced muscle body aches, fever and continued with headaches. I went to a walk-in clinic, where a Covid-19 test was performed and it was negative. The itch on my arma I was able to ignore but the itch on my palms started to spread to my fingers like small blisters and between my fingers.  Very itchy.  It did not spread to any other parts of my body except one toe, which had one blister.  Only thing used at the time was Benedryl.  After a week in a half the blisters dried up and peeled off.        After my second shot, I noticed itchy palms once again, after 2 weeks, of the shot..  This time it spread on the palms of my hands, between my fingers and on my feet.  My doctor gave me a steroid cream, which only seemed to make it worse. Spreading like a rash around my fingernail and under my  nails.   I was also given a scabies lotion even though the doctor didn't think it was scabies. That lotion did calm the itch but it didn't go away.  I continue to use Benedryl now that half of the blisters are dring up.   It was 2 weeks of itch and on the third week it is now beginning to dry up.

Two days after my second Covid-19 shot, I had to inject myself with my Aimovig shot (for migraines). I take the shot in my upper left thigh, first thing in the morning. I got a migraine at about 10:00 p.m. Sometimes I get a mild headache after the shot. Not usually a migraine, though. I took my rescue drug (Butabital, which I've been taking for about a year with no negative side effects) and went to bed. Around 1:00 or 2:00 a.m. I woke up with hives all around my Aimovig injection site. I have taken Aimovig for about a year and this is the first time I've had a reaction to the shot. I didn't know if there was any connection to the timing of the Covid-19 shot two days earlier or not. I took an OTC allergy medication and went back to sleep. The hives and the headache were gone in the morning. The day after the Covid shot I had joint pain, and a 100.9 degree fever. I had a mild rash at the Covid injection site for about 2 days after the shot, which would overlap with the Aimovig injection.
OTHER_MEDS: Aimovig, Losartan, Amliodipine, Pristiq, Buspar, Vitamin D, Junel
HISTORY: High Blood Pressure, High Cholesterol, Anxiety/Depression

In addition her face is discolored and she said she had little to no blood flow in her lower arms and hands. I went to the ER and was immediately admitted to the hospital with a dx of Shingles. My left eye and left ear were beginning to swell shut, with an increasing headache. Also, severe Covid like symptoms were experienced with the first dose of the vaccine.

About 3 minutes after receiving the vaccine while the patient was waiting the recommended 15 minutes post-vaccination, the patient begain to experience symptoms of faintness. She tapped on our window to alert us but almost immediately began to fall out of her chair. Another patient being vaccinated at the time was able to catch the patient and support her head to keep it from hitting the ground. The patient was still alert, responsive, and in a sitting position on the ground when I reached her moments later. The patient shortly collapsed all the way to the ground; we were still able to support her head. We called 911. I rolled the patient to her back. I was able to find a pulse and was able to see the patient's chest rising with breaths. The patient still responded to verbal cues nodding that she could hear me. I removed her face covering to help ventilation. I checked the patient's blood pressure and it was within normal range. Within about 3 minutes the patient was considerably more alert. She asked for some water which we provided. Shortly thereafter she was able to stand with our assistance and return to her chair. EMS arrived and conducted an evaluation; they determined that she did not need to be transported to the hospital. The patient rested in her chair for approximately 15 minutes longer before departing.

Client also reports feeling nervous and anxious prior to receiving second dose of COVID vaccine today.  Vital signs:  blood pressure 165/100, pulse 80, respirations 12 @ 3:23pm.  Client is able to talk and answer questions, no labored breathing noted.  Vital signs @ 3:34 pm;  blood pressure 155/95, pulse 80, respirations 12.  Client reports that symptoms have lessened but continue.  Client denies any medical history, no medication and no allergies.  Client reports no symptoms with first dose of COVID vaccine.  At 3:45 pm RN makes client aware that will call EMS, client refuses, states "I have been dealing with these symptoms for a week now and do not want to have ambulance check me out, I would like to go home."  RN instructs client to dial 911 if symptoms worsen at  home.  At 3:49pm, client leaves against medical advice, her son is with her.  Client able to walk with steady gait.

Initial side effect of significant swelling to affected arm and hand, resolving by morning. 24 hours post injection, awoke with headache comparable to having been hit in head with baseball bat (this continues to be ongoing 3 weeks later). Fever of 100.4, resolved after 1 day. Nausea, increased blood glucose. Continued fatigue and muscle pain/weakness. Following day my scalp, upper back/shoulder blades down arms to finger tips were burning as though I was on fire. This has been relentless. Beginning the second week, it has spread to my ears, several inches down my torso and includes the front of my body as well. Extremely sensitive to touch, including clothing and increased temperature (standing next to someone/ walking outside). There is immense pressure/pain that comes and goes in all of these areas as though they are in a vice. It is at its worst in the evening and first thing in the morning depending on how I slept (ie: if I lay on my stomach, my entire abdomen has so much pressure and pain for the first hour or two I literally can not stand it ? same if I sleep on my back, etc). It is increased by even minimal exertion such as walking around the house. I have missed an extensive amount of work at this point because I am sent home almost every shift. For the first two weeks I had additional worrisome symptoms that were fortunately relieved with an increased, second course of prednisone. The first being intermittent difficulty with reading comprehension, basic math, spelling, following directions, etc. I am still mentally sluggish but it is not alarming as it once was. The other major concern regarded my heart. Particularly at night, with no apparent arrhythmia, I could feel a sensation that led me to believe my heart was not functioning properly. There was an unusual sensation accompanied by slight discomfort, seemingly exacerbated by the muscle relaxer I have taken nightly for at least a year. My anxiety and irritability worsened 24 hours after injection but to be fair I am unsure if that is related to vaccine or the symptoms themselves.   I have been to the ER and have seen 2 additional physicians, including my PCP twice. I have tried three courses of steroids, one at 20 mg x 7 days, two at 30 mg x 5 days. The ER gave me an IM injection of Ketorolac. As of yesterday, I have begun taking Lyrica, increased Topamax and added topical Diclofenac. I was also instructed to take Tylenol around the clock and tizanidine three times daily.
OTHER_MEDS: Tizanidine, Topamax, Lithium, Metformin, Ramelteon, Diclofenac, Atenolol, Tenex, Lovaza, Glyset, Protonix
HISTORY: Diabetes, Hyperlipidemia, Bipolar, Anxiety, GERD, Tachycardia

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 2/3/21, I arrived for my COVID -19 2nd Moderna dose at Hospital. The woman who was administering the dosage asked me to reposition 3 times. She seemed rather flustered and kept saying "she couldn't get the right angle." I had on a polo shirt with the sleeve rolled up above my shoulder to allow for adequate deltoid access. On the 2nd reposition she mentioned that she "may need me to stand up." On the 3rd reposition she had me turn so my back was toward her and she said "ok we got it." She then put the needle in and I immediately knew it was in the wrong spot. It felt extremely high and was the back of my shoulder. As she started injecting it I had a shooting pain go down my arm into my 1st and 2nd fingers. As she was finishing she stated "did that hurt?" "that looked like it hurt." I reported it hurt to her. She stated "She was sorry." My arm was very sore after the first injection so I had hoped that It was just going to be the same and maybe it would be fine despite it being extremely high and in the back of the shoulder. The  pain persisted to the point that I could barely lift my arm by that evening, which continued over the next 5 days. Ibuprofen took the edge off the pain. The pain persisted over the next week in which I contacted my supervisor and reported the incident due to receiving the vaccine at my place of employment. There was pain going into my deltoid, shooting pain in the lateral border of my scapula, throbbing in the shoulder at rest. Due to pain all the muscles tightened up and caused left sided neck pain and headaches. Significant difficulty with dressing, bathing, inability to sleep well, unable to lift arm past 60 degrees of flexion or abduction at shoulder without significant pain. Unable to lift anything in the left arm. Pain slowly improved with PT and use of meloxicam and at current date 5/4/21 still unable to lift items >5lb or bear a lot of weight on the L arm. Continuing to have difficulty at work, unable to do certain mobs/manipulations due to the inability to push/pull.
LAB_DATA: 2/8/21- reported to direct supervisor, 2/12/21 -formal meeting with nurse and reporting of event 2/13/21 - first ortho appointment - recommended steroids 6 day pak 3/2021 - started physical therapy 4/6/21 - ortho follow- up - continued pain recommend MRI 4/15/21 - MRI of Left shoulder 4/27/21 - ortho followup - continued PT March, April, and into May 2021 (present)
OTHER_MEDS: occasional ibuprofen, 3-4x per week powdered collagen
CUR_ILL: B DeQuervains and B hand pain

I woke up 4/26/21 with what looked like 2 bug bites on my left cheek.  By morning of 4/27/21, it was completely swollen.  I experienced itching, pain & vibrating pulses in this area.  The swelling enlarged over the next several days.  On 4/22/21, I had gone to my annual dermatology appt at Derm.  I had to have 2 spots frozen off my face.  One on my left cheek & one on my forehead.  Since the swelling was occurring near the area I had frozen on my left cheek, I called Dr at Derm & was seen by them for a wound check follow up on 4/28/21.  She did not know what it was but did not think it was related to her procedure.  She took a culture & had it tested.  Her best guess was that it was either an infection or Shingles.  Since the results of the culture was going to take several days, she gave me a RX for ValACYclovir.  This was just in case it was shingles.  Even with this medication, the swelling, itching, burning & pulsating continued.  On 5/4/21, I woke up & noticed a significant reduction in the swelling on my left cheek.  I also received a follow up message from Dr that the results showed negative for Shingles.  However, they have no idea what caused the issue on my left cheek.  She recommended that I notify CDC as it may or may not be related to the Covid shot.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 30 Apr, 2nd day after vaccination, I an episode of heart palpitations ("ventricular premature complexes in a pattern of bigeminy").  These were captured on an EKG during a VA disability exam, and started shortly after providing a blood sample (I'm nervous with needles).  Previous day (1st day after vaccination) I had a fever of 101.5 F and was fatigued.  Suspect the stress of the fever, immune response, and then blood sample caused a stress event that triggered an abnormal heart rhythm.  Palpitations not accompanied by light headedness or shortness of breath, so no immediate medical care directed.  Episodes of palpitations continued for 4 days, but have mostly disappeared since.

Dose 1:   45 minutes after shot: slight swelling of airways; breathing difficulty. Congestion lasted roughly an hour.   10 hours: slight nausea, dizziness and possible fever. Slept it off and woke up fine.   Dose 2:   About 3 hours after injection the worst swelling of airways I've experienced. Slight panic arose from being unable to breathe freely. Was making plans to go to the ER when breathing became easier. It was all in all a very strange experience. Airways remained somewhat contracted for about an hour but faded without anything noteworthy.   6 hours after injection severe arm pain.   About 10 hours after the shot i experienced the worst feeling fever i have had. Did not take temp. Serious chills. I was under piles of blankets. Quite disoriented. Felt the need to move but was completely wracked with pain in all my joints.  Despite that I couldn't sit still. I am a complete stranger to insomnia. No medication has ever induced it.  However, this night I simply couldnt sleep more than 10 minutes at a time.  Finally took extra ibuprofen and my body seemed to respond well and the pain and chill subsided. I was achey and exhausted but couldn't sleep. I was also quite nauseous. About 36 hours after first dose i mostly seemed back to normal.    I think it was 6 days later i got hit with the same vertigo and dizziness that preceded my fevers. It's so bizarre. It happens mildly throughout the day but around 10pm or later it hits me hard and is debilitating. I have to stop whatever I'm doing just to lay down. There's no chance of walking without falling unless I have a wall to guide me. The worst of it passes in about 10-15 minutes but lasts about a full hour. Then I'm just nauseous but otherwise fine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Shortly after getting the shot she reported feeling "off" as she was driving she started feeling short of breath and her heart was racing. When she got home around 5 PM she was still feeling short of breath and reported that her heart was racing. She was unable to speak clearly, but was stating that it was due to be being short of breath.  She also reported feeling lethargic and fell asleep until the next morning. She slept until approximately 12 pm the next day. When she woke up she reported feeling right sided cheek tingling. At that time she thought she had just slept wrong. When she attempted to walk down stairs she was limping and reported just feeling very weak on her left side. On Wednesday she slept in late again complaining of lethargy. When she awoke that Wednesday (3/10) her speech was markedly slurred. She was also saying things that didn't make sense. She was dragging her left leg when she tried to walk. We immediately took her to the ER and she was worked up for stroke. When she was triaged in the ER we mentioned that she had just had her COVID vaccine and voiced concerned that maybe she had a reaction to her COVID vaccine. She was admitted to hospital on 3/10 for a possible stroke.  Her MRI was done later on 3/11, Her MRI showed that she has strokes on both sides of her brain in the frontal, parietal and occipital lobes. The doctor referred to her stroke as being caused by a "showering of clots". The doctor said this usually only happens to someone with cardiac issues. My mom has no cardiac history. Her doctor ordered an 2D Echo of her heart and no abnormalities were found (3/12).   She is still disabled from her stroke. She was hospitalized from 3/10 - 3/16. She was the discharged to other care facility from 3/16-3/26. She is currently needing outpatient rehab in a day neuro program. She attends this at outpatient facility. She has to walk with a cane due to persistent left leg weakness. Her speech has a slight slur, and she suffers from short term memory loss. She intermittently has trouble with her equilibrium and reports feeling dizzy. She sometimes has a hard time swallowing or says that it doesn't feel right when  she swallows. She also trouble with word retrieval. She has left-sided neglect which correlates  left eye visual deficits. She currently requires care from a general physician, neurologist, physical therapist, occupational therapist, speech therapist, neuro ophthalmologist and neuo psychologist. She was started on a new medication regime 325 mg aspirin daily, plavix for 21 days (now completed), metformin, amlodipine, coreg and losartan. She is going to need outpatient rehab until at least June from the last update we received from her rehab doctor.
LAB_DATA: CT Scan (3/10) old stroke. She had one years earlier. MRI (3/11)  strokes on both sides of her brain in the frontal, parietal and occipital lobes. 2D Echo (312) Normal heart function

Approximately 3 weeks following my 2nd dose of the Pfizer vaccine, I experienced two days of diarrhea (April 29-30). On May 1, I broke out into hives for seemingly no reason, starting at my joints (knees, elbows, wrists, ankles, cervical spine) which quickly spread to the rest of my body, covering approximately 80% of my skin. I have never had a rash like this in my life (aside from Chicken Pox as a child), and am not aware of any allergens that could have caused me to breakout in this manner. I do not have seasonal allergies. My only food allergy is to bananas, which causes a mild tingling sensation in my mouth/throat and upset stomach, but does not cause anaphylaxis. I did not knowingly ingest or was exposed to bananas at the time my rash presented. The hives were extremely itchy and although I have been medicating with Zyrtec and Benadryl, the rash has only started to recede today (Day 4).

Narrative:

On March 24, 20211 began to feel a numbness in the right side of my face. The next morning, March  25th, I woke to find that my face had dropped and was completely numb. I immediately went to the  Dr.s office and was only able to see a PA. My Primary Physician ordered a brain CT to rule  out a stroke. The PA prescribed Prednisone and Valacyclovir. It took 3 weeks for my face return to  normal but I can still feel a little bit of numbness in my right cheek.  My brain CT was negative for a stroke so it was determined that the Bell's Palsy was a result of a  negative reaction to the Covid shot.

ESCALATING PAIN IN LOWER BACK; ESCALATING PAIN IN LEG; BLOOD CLOT IN LEG; VACCINE-INDUCED IMMUNE THROMBOTIC THROMBOCYTOPENIA; This spontaneous report received from a patient via a company representative (media article) concerned a 4 decade old male (man in 30s). The patient's weight, height, and medical history were not reported. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: Unknown) dose was not reported, frequency once total, administered on 08-APR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. The batch number was not reported. The Company is unable to perform follow-up to request batch/lot numbers. No concomitant medications were reported.  On an unspecified date in APR-2021, within two weeks after receiving a dose of the J&J COVID-19 Vaccine, the patient experienced blood clot in leg. Patient began to experience escalating pain in the lower back and leg on 16-APR-2021. Patient was hospitalized on 21-APR-2021 with escalating pain in his lower back and leg, 13 days after taking the vaccine. It was reported that this was the first male patient with VITT (vaccine-induced immune thrombotic thrombocytopenia) syndrome. The patient was recuperating and making good progress and would be discharged within a few days. Patient's bloodwork showed signature low levels of platelets and fibrinogen, a blood-clotting factor made in the liver, which had been seen in other patients with vaccine-induced clots. Bloodwork showed the patient had the same syndrome as the other patients although initial imaging did not show a blood clot. Physicians later discovered a tiny clot.  The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient was recovering from escalating pain in lower back, escalating pain in leg, blood clot in leg, and vaccine-induced immune thrombotic thrombocytopenia. This report was serious (Hospitalization Caused / Prolonged, and Other Medically Important Condition). This case, from the same reporter is linked to 20210451418.  Initial information was processed with additional information received on 28-APR-2021.; Sender's Comments: V0: This spontaneous report received from a media article concerned a man in 30s who experienced vaccine-induced thrombotic thrombocytopenia 13 days after vaccine. Medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. Eight days after vaccine, patient began to experience escalating pain in the lower back and leg. Initial imaging did not show a blood clot but physicians later discovered a "tiny clot" in the leg. Thirteen days after vaccine, patient was hospitalized with escalating pain in his lower back and leg. The patient was recuperating and making good progress and would be discharged within a few days. Patient's bloodwork showed "signature low levels of platelets and fibrinogen." Although the other risk factors (not reported) may have contributed, based on evolving knowledge of Thrombosis with Thrombocytopenia Syndrome (TTS, per definition from Brighton Collaboration - BC) and considering the low platelet count and temporal relationship to vaccination (BC Criteria level 1), the s events are assessed to have a plausible relationship with vaccination. Reporter contact information was not provided which precludes meaningful additional information in this version.

I went to see my ENT specialist on Monday, 5/1/2021. I had a full audiology work up and meeting with my ENT. The exam so that I had 100% hearing loss in my right ear.   I am having an MRI on Weds 5/12 and meeting again with my ENT on 5/18.   I was put on a high dose of steroids, Prednisone, for the next  2 weeks. trying to get back some hearing.
LAB_DATA: Audiology test and pressure test. 5/3/2021, confirmed 100% loss of hearing in right ear. No fluid, no obstruction. Idiopathic Sensory Hearing Loss.
