I had the second Moderna shot that afternoon, scheduled for 4:15pm but it was about 4:30pm when I got it.  I moved around as instructed by my doc, and after 15 minutes went back to my car.  I noticed after another several minutes that my pulse was still elevated so opted to go back in and talk to a health care professional.  Pulse was 120.  Paramedic wanted me to lie down in waiting area but I didn't want to be in such a potentially  germy environment, and the guy next to me who had fainted earlier was just getting up himself.  She walked me back to my car, where I agreed to wait, listen to a stress relief hypnosis audio and see if my pulse rate would calm down.  She came back out w/ a BP cuff and said my blood pressure was 210 over 130 (or some number over 100; I don't recall which) and she said I needed to get in an ambulance right away and go to the hospital.  I said I would make my own decisions about my body and I wanted to try a couple of other things first, promised not to leave, contacted my doctor, naturopath.  (Note: I did not have any other worrisome symptoms -- blurred vision, dizziness, etc.  My head was a little buzzy, but whether out of fear or in reaction to the shot I didn't know.  I was a little flushed).  He asked me a bunch of questions, said my body hadn't had time to mount an immune response to the vaccine and that I had likely had a histamine reaction to a preservative in the vaccine (or similar), which a couple of his other patients had experienced.  He asked if I'd been drinking fluids (yes, plenty), had eaten recently (no, so he suggested I have some food; I had some nuts, a little cheese and some Cheez-Its so had that), asked if I had an antihistamine around -- I did, but I don't do well with Benadryl and didn't have Claritin, but after looking through my bag found some Allervive, an herbal product he compounds.  He said, "That's perfect."  I took two of the three capsules and hung up.  Staff were checking up on me in my car every ten minutes or so, by the way, very kind and professional as I had been quite upset at the whole "get in an ambulance" scenario.  He thought some of my reaction was probably also stress-related, and I noticed before the shot that I was teary, not from anxiety but the kind you get when you feel relief after a long ordeal.  I didn't feel anxiety, really, until the first blood pressure measurement.  He also let me know that if the bottom number didn't drop below 100 they couldn't let me go.  After eating, drinking some more water and taking the Allervive my BP was down to 138 over 75 in just a few minutes.  I agreed to stick around and make sure it stuck.  We re-tested again about 15 minutes later, perhaps longer, and it was the same.  I had been a little flushed but that had gone away too.  I left and went for a light walk and eventually drove home without incident.  I had symptoms after the shot that could have been related to my body fighting off the allergic reaction or to the vaccine itself, but they were pretty mild (fatigue later that night; occasional heart rate elevation sometimes after eating or with very mild exertion -- not unusual for me if I'm "fighting off" something; sore, itchy, red blotch sized between a quarter and a half dollar at vaccination site -- it is still a little tender today and appears a bit bruised; a bit sinus headache-y for three days, especially when I bent down to tie my shoes or something like that - also not that unusual as I often seem to "cleanse" through my sinuses when I have a bug or am fighting something off).    In hindsight, I think the symptoms I had after the first shot, which lasted about 9 hours, may have been fighting off the allergic reaction and not a reaction to the virus vaccine itself.
OTHER_MEDS: Montelkast, Spironolactone, herbal hormone tincture compounded by naturopath, herbal thyroid supplement, herbal liver cleanse supplement, mood support, compound hormone capsules, progesterone cream, vaginal compounded estrogen cream, Albute

I couldn?t bend or move my legs. My wrists were bent down and my fingers all locked together. I could not move them at all. I was screaming out in pain. It was the worst pain I?ve ever felt. My roommate called 911. Paramedics arrived and took my temperature and blood pressure. They tried calming me down. eventually I did. And my fingers and legs unlocked but I continued having a severe headache, back pain, muscle aches and nausea. I woke up every hour of the night and threw up several times.  It?s been 24 hours after the shot and I am still having headaches fatigue and muscle spasms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Chest Pain; Dry mouth; Could not start hydrated; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of CHEST PAIN (Chest Pain) in a 56-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 008B21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     No Medical History information was reported.    On 25-Mar-2021 at 1:45 PM, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 25-Mar-2021, the patient experienced DRY MOUTH (Dry mouth). 25-Mar-2021, the patient experienced DEHYDRATION (Could not start hydrated). On 28-Mar-2021, the patient experienced CHEST PAIN (Chest Pain) (seriousness criterion hospitalization). The patient was hospitalized from 09-Apr-2021 to 10-Apr-2021 due to CHEST PAIN. On 10-Apr-2021, DRY MOUTH (Dry mouth) and DEHYDRATION (Could not start hydrated) had resolved. On 12-Apr-2021, CHEST PAIN (Chest Pain) had resolved with sequelae.      DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 09-Apr-2021, Blood pressure measurement: 192/99 (abnormal) 192/99. On 09-Apr-2021, Troponin: elevated (Inconclusive) elevated troponin levels.     The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown.       Concomitant medications were not reported.  On 25Mar2021, the patient reported initial minor side effects of dry mouth while sitting in her car, but no other noteworthy side effects immediately following injection. Then, 2 or 3 days later the patient experienced chest pain that she reported started out as very mild, however, it grew in intensity over the following weeks, and she presented to the Emergency Room (ER) on Friday, 09Apr2021 per the caller's estimation.  Blood pressure taken at the ER was 192/99mmHg.  Full hospital work-up performed with the patient noted that she was negative for blood clots but had elevated troponin levels.  She said the hospital staff evaluated her heart's condition and found no sign of a heart attack.  On 10Apr2021, she was discharged with a new prescription of metoprolol. On the Monday after discharge, the patient had felt symptoms of chest pain again along with elevated blood pressure levels, so she returned to the ER where she was discharged without hospitalization and given a clonidine patch for any future blood pressure fluctuations.  Since then she had visited her Cardiologist and he has substituted her prescription metoprolol for amlodipine and losartan combination therapy, and to discontinue her prescription for clonidine patches.  Patient indicated her cardiologist is hopeful that her blood pressure should normalize over time and instructed patient not to receive her second dose of the vaccine. Additionally, patient reported that, from the time she received her vaccination, until she was discharged, she could not start hydrated.  She reported drinking large quantities of water, electrolyte replacement liquids, and Gatorade with no success.   Event of chest pain was resolved with Sequelae of elevated blood pressure.  Treatment included clonidine patches and metoprolol  On an unspecified date, the clonidine patches and metoprolol were stopped and amlodipine and losartan combination therapy was started.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Within a week (I believe the timing), she began to feel migrating pain and stiffness around her body and was very lethargic. She had aches and often stiffness in her legs and arms, a dry cough, and night sweats. Her mouth became parched. Her eyes had suffered from dryness in the past and became even more acute. At first, her primary care physician, Dr.(name) did not recognise her symptoms, didn't order any tests, and sent her to physical therapy. Dr. (Name withheld) Put her on Meloxicam for inflammation and the issues mostly have subsided except for continuing pain in her arms. Since mid-Jan, Dr. (Name withheld) had referred her to an ophthalmologist, gastroenterologist and rheumatologist. Patient had an appointment schedule with a pneumologist on 21Apr. The gastroenterologist did an endoscopy and has ordered a CT Scan to rule out lymphoma. The rheumatologist was running more test. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Bell's palsy; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (the patient). This 51-year-old female patient received BNT162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE; Lot Number: UNKNOWN), via an unspecified route of administration in the left arm, upper arm, on 06Apr2021 14:00 (at the age of 51-year-old) as single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The patient did not receive any other vaccines within four weeks prior to the vaccination. The patient denied being sick at the time of vaccination. The patient's medical history was not reported. No relevant family medical history was reported. There were no concomitant medications. On the night of 08Apr2021, the patient was having intense pain down her neck and behind her left ear, and it has been waking her up at night. On 09Apr2021, she went to Urgent Care and they misdiagnosed her with a possible oncoming ear infection. On Saturday morning (10Apr2021), she woke up and could not move the left side of her face so she went to the ER (emergency room) and they diagnosed her with Bell's Palsy. On 10Apr2021 at the ER, blood test for Lyme disease was negative. The ER gave the patient a steroid and antiviral pill and told her to follow up with her primary doctor in 8 days. The patient went to her physician's office on 19Apr2021 to follow-up with her Bell's Palsy. The patient stated that intense pain (down her neck and behind her left ear) was apparently a symptom of the Bell's Palsy. The only improvement with the Bell's Palsy was that she can sip out of straw a little easier but lips are still to the side. The clinical outcome of the event Bell's Palsy was resolving.  The lot number for the vaccine, BNT162b2, was not provided and will be requested during follow-up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Blood clots in her nose; Nose bleed; her arms are both numb on her; Couldn't move them; She feels lethargic; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient herself) via a medical information team. A female patient of an unspecified age received first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE, Formulation: Solution for injection), via an unspecified route of administration on an unspecified date as a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. It was reported that, enquired have people died from the vaccine or not. Enquired what do you know about the news in the media about reports of death in nursing home elderly patients. Response: Pfizer and BioNTech are aware of reported deaths following administration of Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine . We are working with the (withheld) to gather all the relevant information. (Withheld) Authorities have prioritized the immunization of residents in Nursing Homes, most of whom are very elderly with underlying medical conditions and some which are terminally ill. (Withheld) confirm the number of incidents so far was not alarming, and in line with expectations. All reported deaths would be thoroughly evaluated by (Withheld) to determine if these incidents are related to the vaccine. (Withheld) Health Authorities have now changed its recommendation in relation to vaccination of the terminally ill (Clinical Frailty Scale 8 or higher). Our immediate thoughts are with the bereaved families. The Global Advisory Committee on Vaccine Safety (GACVS) COVID-19 Vaccine Safety subcommittee met virtually on Tuesday, 19Jan2021, to review available information and data on deaths reported in frail, elderly individuals who had received the Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 mRNA vaccine, BNT162b2 (hereafter, BNT162b2). Experts invited from the (Withheld) and the (Withheld) provided an overview of deaths reported in (Withheld) and in the WHO global database (VigiBase) following vaccination with BNT162b2." Based on a careful scientific review of the information made available, the subcommittee came to the following conclusions: The current reports do not suggest any unexpected or untoward increase in fatalities in frail, elderly individuals or any unusual characteristics of adverse events following administration of BNT162b2. Reports are in line with the expected, all-cause mortality rates and causes of death in the sub-population of frail, elderly individuals, and the available information does not confirm a contributory role for the vaccine in the reported fatal events. In view of this, the committee considers that the benefit-risk balance of BNT162b2 remains favourable in the elderly, and does not suggest any revision, at present, to the recommendations around the safety of this vaccine." Enquired what was the efficacy after one dose. Caller had a terrible experience after her first dose of the Pfizer BioNTech COVID19 vaccine. She had blood clots in her nose, every time she blew her nose, blood clots would come out. She never had a nose bleed before. She also added that her arms are both numb on her. She couldn't move them, she feels lethargic. She's supposed to get her second dose next Friday. Enquired do we have any information regarding blood clots or not. Caller was upset and disconnected the call before some of the answers were given. Caller also asked the following questions: Has there been deaths reported from the vaccine or not, what was the efficacy after 1 dose, any guidance on getting the second dose after having side effects after the first dose. Response: Proposed response : CONS-Blood clots. Caller said "this was ridiculous" when I tried providing her with a long website with more information. She feels like we are withholding information from the public. She thinks the deaths should have been on the media. Caller hung up. Enquired do you have any guidance on getting the second dose after having side effects with the first dose. I had a side effect after the first dose of the vaccine. Should I get the second dose or not. Caller disconnected before agent could provide response. Response: Proposed response: As noted in the Fact Sheet for Recipients, you should not get the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine if you had a severe allergic reaction after a previous dose of the vaccine or if you had a severe allergic reaction to any ingredient of the vaccine. The decision to receive the second dose for any other reason could not be made by Pfizer. We refer you to speak to your healthcare provider about the risks of the vaccine compared to the risks of potentially not being fully protected against COVID-19 infection. Your healthcare provider knows your health situation and has access to information that can better help inform this decision. The outcome of the events was unknown.  No follow-up attempts are needed. Information about lot/batch number cannot be obtained.

Premature rupture of membranes; Intra-uterine death; Laboratory test normal; Premature labour; 27-year-old pregnant female patient received a injection of ADACEL; Upon internal review on 19-Apr-2021, the case 2010-01165 was incorrectly created for fetus from current case will be deleted and all information merged in current case  SERIOUSNESS CRITERIA: OTHER - MEDICALLY SIGNIFICANT  Initial report received 08 July 2009 from a health care professional.   A 27-year-old pregnant female patient with a history of a latex allergy, had received a 0.5mL injection of Adacel (lot number, route and site not reported) on 07 July 2009. Her date of last menstrual period was not reported; however, her expected date of confinement was estimated to be 30 January 2010. She had two previous full term pregnancies with normal outcomes. She had not been taking any concomitant medications at the time of vaccination.  At the time of the report, the patient had not experienced any adverse events since receiving Adacel.   Follow-up information was received 19 February 2010 from a health care professional.   Based upon new information received, this case now meets seriousness criteria and has been upgraded from non serious to serious.  According to the reporter, the patient was reported to have been in good health. She had no illness at the time of vaccination and she had not received any other vaccines within four weeks of receiving Adacel (lot number, route, and site not reported).  The patient had a history of two prior pregnancies, both which resulted in full term live births with no congenital anomalies.  Her last menstrual period occurred 26 April 2009 and her estimated date of delivery had been 31 January 2010 (previously reported as 30 January 2010).   Prenatal testing had been normal.  On 22 August 2009, 46 days post vaccination, the patient delivered a male fetus vaginally at 22 weeks gestation weighing 296 grams (0.296 kilograms) with no congenital anomalies. Apgar scores were 0 / 0 at one and five minutes respectively; outcome was demise. The patient had not experienced any complications during labor and/or delivery. Per the reporter, it was not known if the patient had experienced any adverse events; however, the reporter further stated that the patient had not experienc ed any problems until delivery at 22 weeks gestation.  According to the reporter, the patient recovered.   Follow-up information received from a health care professional on 18 March 2010.   The patient had received the Adacel (lot number UF460BA, Sanofi Pasteur SA lot number C3066) intramuscular in the left deltoid.    Follow-up information was received on 19 April and 20 April 2010 from a health care professional.  According to the reporter, prenatal testing had not been performed (previously reported with results of normal findings). Fetal demise had been known prior to birth and an autopsy had not been performed. The onset of preterm labor was 22 August 2009. Per the reporter, the etiology for both preterm labor and early fetal death was reported as premature rupture of membranes. According to the reporter, the patient recovered on 22 August 2009.    Documents held by sender: None  Additional information was received on 19-Apr-2021 regarding an unsolicited valid serious case from other healthcare professional via the health authority (Vaers ID: 381304).  Events intra-uterine death, and laboratory test normal were added. Event coding of premature delivery updated to premature labour and considered non-serious.  The patient had not been taking any concomitant medications at the time of vaccination. From information received 19 February 2010, the patient had no concurrent illness at the time of vaccination, no maternal drug exposures, and she had not received any other vaccines within four weeks of receiving ADACEL.   On 07-Jul-2009, the patient received a 0.5 mL dose of suspect DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE [ADACEL] (lot C3066 and expiry date: 08-Aug-2010) via intramuscular route in the left deltoid for prophylactic vaccination. While patient was 10 week pregnant.  On an unknown date, the patient developed a non-serious laboratory test normal, following the administration of DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE. The patient visited to emergency department.  On an unknown date the patient experienced serious intra-uterine death (foetal death) following the administration of DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE. This event was assessed as medically significant and the patient visited to emergency department.  On 22-AUG-2009, the patient developed a non-serious premature labour, one month 15 days following the administration of DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE. The patient visited to emergency department.  It was case of vaccine exposure during pregnancy (exposure during pregnancy) (latency same day). While patient was 10 week pregnant  It was unknown if patient received any corrective treatment.  The patient was recovered from the events.; Sender's Comments: This case concerns a 27 years old female patient who experienced premature delivery, premature rupture of membranes, foetal death, premature labour, and exposure during pregnancy, after vaccination with ADACEL. The time to onset is not compatible for premature labour and premature delivery whereas unknown for rest of the events. The patient was in good condition during vaccination. The patient's medical history, concomitant medication, medical condition at time of vaccination and other lab test ruling out alternate etiologies were not reported. Based upon the reported information, the role of vaccine cannot be assessed.

LAB_DATA: Sonogram at hospital ER  4/27/21. ****important. In mt description I put wrong date on beginning of adverse reaction after shingles shot had flipped my calendar and can?t go back on this report. Mouth burning Sat April 24 2021. At primary Dr nd ER both on Tuesday 4/27/21
CUR_ILL: I am 65 years old. I just went on vars reporting system and it says if shots were over six weeks ago I could not participate, but I just read that adverse reactions can happen after that date. I also have a possible second theory on my adverse reaction that happened to me last week, went to my primary, mentioned it to pharmacy where I got second dose of shingles and needed up at hospital Er, and mentioned reporting...but no one seemed to decide to report from their end and if they did, I was not told. I had my first Pfizer shot at shopping center 2/3/21. Only mild symptoms mainly at shot arm. Second COVID same place 2/24/21. I did have fatigue that started that evening from a morning shot and had a headache that lasted the second day after shot. I had my first Shingrix shingles shot in Oct 2020. Normally one gets second shingles in six months. With COVID hitting I concentrated on that...the COVID shots listed above. After second COVID I asked pharmacist about when to get second shingles. They suggested I wait at least two weeks. I was told second shingles shot is tougher by them, and many retired friend I know. I am an active adult, finally getting back to the gym after COVID shots and playing some tennis. I decided to wait a little longer and had my second Shingrix shot 4/5/2021. This hit me hard. I was in bed for four days. Fever, chills, adverse stomach pain, headache...flu symptoms. I do go to a Dr. I have Barrett?s esophagus and take famotidine twice a day. The stomach pain got severe. I went to health clinic and the nurse practitioner put me on Dexilant for two weeks only. I have bad osteoporosis and osteoarthritis.....inherited. Along with my career in the school system I was a certified fitness instructor, aerobics, weights, step, water...up until age 52. After my cervical fusion I stopped teaching, but continued as always to work out in the gym and play league tennis. I?ve gone to pain management since then and keep my cortisone shots to a min on my hip, hands and cervical because of bone density. Saturday 4/22 my mouth started feeling sore. By Sunday it was burning pain. Could hardly eat and brushing my teeth was excruciating. Monday I called my dentist to cancel my six month teeth cleaning. I started reading about delayed COVID adverse reaction and shingles shot adverse reactions. On Tuesday morning 8am I went to my primary Dr at Medical center. The inside of mouth all red. My lips and face were swollen, even my tongue had numbness.Talked about shots, also herpes....which I have never had. One partner and husband for 45 years. They put me on a prednisone pack and told me to take Benadryl. I was also having cramping in my right calf. Figured I was dehydrated at was working at drinking a lot of water. By 3pm husband was not home. Cramping in right calf got worse. Drove myself to Hospital ER center across street. They did a sonogram to make sure I was not getting a blood clot. It was negative and went home to continue prednisone regiment. Woke up Wed morning with a sheath of blisters in my mouth. It was painful and it seems I had broken out with a case of shingles in my mouth. Obviously I called the Dr. I was making sure it was not going to my throat or affecting my breathing. Now a week later my mouth is better and off prednisone. My personal theory is either I had a delayed reaction to COVID shots, or a severe reaction to second shingles shot or a combination of my immune system being overloaded with work producing antibodies that by the time I got the second shingles shot five weeks after second COVID at age 65 it was too much. I want to be contacted on both reaction accountability for COVID and Shingrix...and possible new thoughts as to how hard having multiple vaccinations so close together. I also feel that the adverse reaction to severe stomach pain and swelling ...etc seemed to be shingrix related with a combination of immune system overload.
HISTORY: Please read entire context. Had both Pfizer COVID shots first 2/3/21 second 2/24/21 then second shingles Shingrix shot 4/5/21. Read entire synapse. Went to my digestive health  dr, went to primary care Dr when adverse reactions occurred after second shingles shot went to Er same day later with more reactions. This was 4/27/21.

Severe Headache; GI Symptoms; Muscle Control Issues; This case was obtained on 12NOV2020 in the review of publications.  Literature Citation:  A study participant (age, gender not reported) received the anthrax vaccine (date, dose, lot not reported) and cited several problems that occurred following injection including muscle control issues (PT: muscle disorder), GI symptoms (PT: gastrointestinal disorder), and severe headache (PT: headache). The time to onset and outcome were not reported. No further information was provided.  Literature Abstract: Most people have no problems when administered vaccines; however, as with all drugs, reported adverse effects (rAEs) do occur. There is a need to better understand the potential predictors of reported vaccine AEs (rVaxAEs), including modifiable (environmental) predictors. Individuals who have Gulf War Illness (GWI) report increased experiences of drug experiences of drug and chemical rAEs, extending to rVaxAEs. Individuals provide an opportunity to examine the relationship between their reported exposures and rAEs. Forty-one individuals with GWI and 40 healthy controls reported exposure and rAEs to exposure, including 14 vaccines. Individual and summed vaccine exposures, rVaxAEs, and reported Vaccine AE Propensity (summed rVaxAEs / Summed vaccine exposures) were compared in cases vs. controls. Exposure-outcome assessments focused on individuals, using a multivariable regression with robust standard error. More designated vaccines were reported in cases than in controls: 9.0 (2.3) vs. 3.8 (2.3), p<0.0001.  The fraction of vaccines received that led to rAEs was ten-fold higher in cases: 0.24 (0.21), vs. 0.023 (0.081), p<0.0001. Multivariable assessment confirmed that radiation and pesticides remained significant statistical predictors of reported Vaccine AE Propensity. Exposure tied to excess rVaxAEs in individuals may contribute to, or underlie, the reported link between rVaxAEs in individuals and later ill health.  Company Comment:  The information received from the article is not specific and refers to a multiple vaccinations that included anthrax vaccine as the most reactogenic and most with reported reactions comparing to other vaccines. However, there was one subject that reported headache and unspecific term of gastrointestinal and muscle disorder post injection. Headache is a known phenomenon that occur post BioThrax injection. Nausea is the only gastrointestinal disorder that has been recorded in clinical studies and postmarketing reports. The report of muscle control issue is too general to define its meaning. Just because the report says that the occurrence was post injection, it is assumed that it was temporal relationship, therefore headache is considered probable but the gastrointestinal and muscle disorder are considered possible, although being an unspecific term the relevance is missing.; Sender's Comments: The information received from the article is not specific and refers to a multiple vaccinations that included anthrax vaccine as the most reactogenic and most with reported reactions comparing to other vaccines. However, there was one subject that reported headache and unspecific term of gastrointestinal and muscle disorder post injection. Headache is a known phenomenon that occur post BioThrax injection. Nausea is the only gastrointestinal disorder that has been recorded in clinical studies and postmarketing reports. The report of muscle control issue is too general to define its meaning. Just because the report says that the occurrence was post injection, it is assumed that it was temporal relationship, therefore headache is considered probable but the gastrointestinal and muscle disorder are considered possible, although being an unspecific term the relevance is missing.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Several hours after the shot, I began to feel very hot all over my face and body. I got very dry to the touch and I became extremely thirsty. I also had full body tremors. When I woke up the next morning (5/4) around 10 a.m., I had a fever, headache, and serious brain fog. My legs ached, especially my hips and knees. The intense thirst and dryness also persisted. I felt lightly nauseous on and off. I took an extra strength Tylenol and drank a lot of water before sleeping again until around 4 p.m.. Once I woke up, I was still suffering from all the aforementioned symptoms, but with less severity. I had another extra strength Tylenol and drank water and a sports drink. I ate a granola bar right after the Tylenol and started to feel a little better. Then I got really hungry, so I ate a muffin and drank an energy+ juice drink that had 80mg caffeine derived from green and black tea. I started to feel a lot better after that, though I was still weak and experiencing aching in my legs and hips. I took another nap from 7 p.m. to 9 p.m. and then ate once more before going to sleep for the night around 1:30 a.m. I have woken up today (5/5) with a slight headache but no other symptoms save the injection site soreness that has also persisted since a few hours after the shot. A note for comparison: as reported, this is my 2nd dose. My first dose had no symptoms whatsoever aside from injection site soreness.
CUR_ILL: Not an illness, but I was on my period. I started it that day
ALLERGIES: Red dye allergy, possible allergy to medications that are part of the cillin group such as Penicillin.

There is a 5mm solid nodule within the right lower lobe best seen on axial image 32 series e. There is a small 6 mm subpleural nodule within the right lower lobe best seen on axial image 43 series 3. Approximately 3 days after receiving 2nd moderna vaccine, I woke-up with my eyes swollen then would not stop watering throughout the day, this turned into eczema on my eyes within days.  During the same time, blotchy rashes appeared all over my face, neck but a different hive-like pattern of rashes appeared on my chest and minimally on my thigh.  I also developed severe dermatitis on my fingers.  They swelled until they blistered and cracked.  The burning and itching was tremendous.  I had never experienced such fatigue either.  I had to wrap my fingers for weeks.  Throughout these symptoms, I went to Urgent Care and was placed on prednisone... it cleared up for about 3 days then returned full blast.  So then I went to dermatology who did an extended prednisone taper (& prescribed hydroxyzine).  Before that treatment course was even completed, symptoms were coming back so I saw a different doctor through my PCP office.  I was given an expensive steroid cream and a long-lasting steroid injection with benedryl.  Finally, the rashes across my face and chest were cleared up.  I was feeling like myself again having normal energy level, but that ended 3-4 days later.  I had a return visit to dermatology where a biopsy was completed (came back as an allergic reaction to either a medication or contact dermatitis).   A friend who's son battled severe eczema then had me try 2 creams for my hands which helped to heal the deep cracks and lose the callused skin; however, it's May 5, 2021 and my hands are flaring up (swollen to the point that 3 fingertips are turning maroon, starting to callus and I imagine will crack open within days again).  My energy levels are no where near my baseline.  I consume an awful lot of caffeine and sleep 10-12 hours a day/night in order to get through work and other tasks.  No one has been able to successfully treat me for 3 months now.    I will add that after my 1st vaccine on 1/7/21, a WEEK later, I had lip, tongue and throat swelling.  I took OTC allergy medicine around the clock for a week and symptoms subsided.  I reported this at the time of my 2nd injection and was told to proceed as it was "delayed" versus anaphylaxis.  I had no health issues prior.  My only known allergies/sensitivities over 38 years was penicillin (hives), cheap metals (rash) and cats... none of these have even came close for comparison of what I suspect the vaccine did to my immune system.  I work in a hospital and am very fearful I will have similar reactions to the flu vaccine now or worst, the COVID vaccine will be mandatory.
LAB_DATA: 3/31/21 biopsy done on chest for this particular rash
PRIOR_VAX: COVID19 (Moderna) 1st injection

I got first shot on Friday April 9. On Monday the 12th, I got small rash on lower left arm, NOT at the injection site, but below it. By Tuesday the rash spread all over my body and got much worse. I was having short episodes of breathlessness and feeling a bit dizzy, and on the 15th I went to ER because the rash was getting worse and was creeping towards my face. The rash was red, kind of looked like a million mosquito bites, caused some swelling, and very itchy in the first few days. I was very uncomfortable and unable to sleep well.  I tried Benadryl before I went to ER but it made me overly tired. At the ER the doctor diagnosed me with allergic reaction to the shot. He prescribed a course of Prednisone to calm the rash. I had a very active rash for OVER two weeks between April 12 to the week of April 26, and there is still remnants of the rash today, which I hope do not reactivate at any time. I could figure out the timeframe of most active rash better by looking at my notes and doctors but that is a general summary.
LAB_DATA: I plan to get an allergy test to see if I am allergic to any ingredient in shot. Not sure if it was an allergic reaction to an ingredient, or a "normal" immune response, or something else. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a male who presents for a 1 month history of numbness, tingling and weakness of the fourth and fifth fingers of the left hand. He presents with his wife who concurs with history. He describes the numbness tingling sensation extending up his left hand into the proximal forearm and what would be the ulnar distribution.  He is noted weakness of the fourth and fifth digits such that he cannot fully grasp with that hand compared to his contralateral hand.  Patient describes more numbness and weakness than frank pain although he has noticed it when he is woken up at night.  He has not taken any specific medication for this.  Patient states this started approximately April eighth ninth or 10th several days after getting his first Pfizer vaccination in the left arm.  That was a Pfizer Lot number EN 8737 expiration July 2021 given on April 6 at the urgent care vaccination site.  Patient feels the vaccine was given behind his deltoid on the shoulder rather than mid deltoid muscle.  He did not have any pain numbness or shooting sensations immediately.  Reports the muscle was a little sore that day or the next but really nothing of significance until several days later. He did not report any significant redness or swelling at the site of the vaccination.  He reports not having any photos of the side of the vaccination but he and his wife did take a photo about a week ago of the area of that he feels is still tender in the posterior shoulder region It is not clear to me whether the soreness in the shoulder extended down to the hand and then improve leaving the hand symptoms or whether soreness disappeared at the time the hand arm symptoms came on. He has not had any similar symptoms he denies having any carpal tunnel or hand problems in the past. Past medical history is pertinent for: some chronic back pain in the thoracic or lumbar region that began after traumatic vertebral fractures following a motor vehicle accident in 2012. he is followed by Dr. of pain specialist of, She is maintained on chronic methadone.  He has had recent lower thoracic or lumbar block with plans to have radioablation therapy to those nerve roots in the next several days. Also has well-controlled hypertension on lisinopril 20 mg and takes 81 mg enteric-coated aspirin daily. Here for evaluation as symptoms have not resolved on their own over the last 3 to 4 weeks
LAB_DATA: Nerve conduction studies and hand therapy pending nerve conduction studies often take 1 to 3 months in this region of the state
CUR_ILL: Patient with chronic thoracolumbar pain after traumatic MVA related thoracolumbar vertebral fractures from 2012.  Receiving injections and radio ablative therapy to local nerves

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3 days after the injection, I was fatigued, and my joints in my arms and legs were sore.  My arms felt so heavy I felt it was an effort to lift them.   This was identical to the way I felt after my first vaccine on 3/11/21.  However, I developed an additional symptom of pain in my right knee.  It became swollen, warm, and there was pain on the backside of the knee as well as the kneecap area.  This became so severe that I could not put any weight on this knee on Sunday afternoon ( 3 full days after shot).  I know I didn't injure the knee because on Saturday we drove  and I was just in the car for 2 days.  It hurt to extend the knee but felt better to elevate it.   A knee brace was not helpful.  IThe pain woke me up almost every night for the last 3 weeks.  Ibuprofen barely helps.  For a couple of days last week, the knee would crack with every step.  This was painful, so I limited walking.  I have been staying off of this leg ever since and am waiting for an appointment with an orthopedist on the 20th.    It is just starting to feel better.  It is still warm but yesterday I finally saw the kneecap peek out.  I am not certain this is from the vaccine and i can only find one journal article describing a "flare up" of rheumatoid arthritis following the shot.  I do not have arthritis (yet) so the article was not helpful.  I have had bursitis in my hip twice but not for over 10 years.  I am getting an Xray tomorrow.

Patient history: Lyme disease and pork allergy. Vaccine given at 0912. At 0925 patient experiencing throat tightness, scratchy throat, cough, and chest tightness. Initial oxygen at 98% pulse 70. Patient denied shortness of breath, dizziness, or feeling lightheaded. Patient escorted to the back area for further assessment. At 0931, 25 mg (10 ml) of benadryl administered orally; no difficulty swallowing. VS: BP 160/98, pulse 75, respiration 18, temp 97.2, oxygen 99%. At 0937, patient verbalizes "throat feels better, scratch still there but no chest tightness. I can breath better." At 0939, patient reports symptoms of throat tightness. Patient auscultated, negative wheezing. Bilateral lungs clear. Benadryl 25 mg (10 ml) po administered without difficulty. 0941 VS: BP 180/114, pulse 74, respiration 18, temp 96.2, and oxygen 98%. Patient continues with symptoms but negative for labored breathing, tachypnea, cyanosis, or swelling. At 0952, BP 170/119, pulse 82, respiration 20, temp 95.9, oxygen 96%. At 0955, symptoms continue of throat tightness and hoarse voice; EMS (911) notified and en route. At 0959, 0.3 mg epinephrine (auto-injector) administered IM via left thigh. At 1006, EMS arrived and patient evaluated. Per patient, "still feel scratchy throat". At 1011, patient transported via stretcher with EMS to hospital for evaluation. At 0957, Medical director made aware and in agreement with transport to hospital for further evaluation.

Progressive lower extremity weakness with markedly diminished reflex: Per the history it appears that patient has had a progressive course of this problem over the last 1 week.  His symptomatology is mostly consistent with gait ataxia with some lower extremity weakness.  He mentions that his weakness of the lower extremities became more and more pronounced towards the end of the week when he would start trembling in his legs whenever standing for some time.  Although he had some numbness and tingling few days ago but that does not seem to be the predominant symptoms.  There was no preceding symptoms of any viremia prior to this.  Although he has Covid in January, however he did not have cough expectorations upper respiratory infection or any diarrhea in the last 1 month.  He has not been exposed to any new pets or any new medications.  His clinical exam suggest a lower extremity weakness more proximal than distal although there appears to be some sensory sparing.  He has diminished reflexes all over including absent reflexes in his lower extremities and many of the upper extremities.  His imaging study did not show any specific etiology for the cause of his problem.  He does not have any spinal etiology and his exam does not show any upper motor type of involvement.  His spinal fluid shows a high protein with no cells consistent with cytoalbuminogenic dissociation.  So he definitely fits with the diagnosis of acute immune mediated demyelinating polyneuropathy or Guillain-Barr� syndrome.  On IVIG therapy.  Overall appears to be some improved however not still able to walk.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Sunday April 25th 2021, I woke up with severe chest pain that went up to the right side of my neck, as well as having shortness of breath.  I was admitted into the ER and they ran blood work, did a CT scan and x ray of My chest. When my bloodwork came back, it showed I had very elevated troponin levels. Because I was having continuous pain, I was given morphine but it didn't work. So they upped it and gave me dilaudid and that took the pain away. It was in the doctors best interest I get transported to a facility with a good cardiatric team. Upon arriving to the new facility, they further drew my blood and ran more tests. I got admitted as an in patient on the cardiatric floor. The cardiologists ordered for me to have an echocardiogram done, another CT scan with a special protocol to view my heart, and an MRI done of my heart.   After my echocardiogram and CT scan came back fine, the doctors said they'd be surprised if the MRI DIDNT show something. When that result came back, it did reveal my heart was still inflamed.   After ruling out all other possibilities they concluded that the 2nd Dose of Moderna COVID vaccination I'd received was the culprit behind my diagnosis. My diagnosis being, a case of myocarditis as well as a mild heart arrhythmia.   For the next several months I am kn a medication called metoprolol 25mg, 2 half tablets a day, to correct my heart arrhythmia and relieve stress from my heart as well as minimize the amount of stress I encounter each day. No heavy lifting pushing or pulling of any sort for the next 3 months.

Swelling was present from the beginning of the episode, but increased over time.  Pain and swelling abated 3 weeks after first vaccine dose for about a week.  Second vaccine dose occurred 3-29-21 and pain/swelling returned.  Pain in heels was still present at this time, but majority of pain migrated to ankles and achilles regions.  Swelling increased by week 5 to become obvious Edema.  Acupuncture did not help.  Stretching did not help.  Rest and elevating feet did not help.  Magnesium supplement may have helped relieve pain, but I am unsure. Compression sock did not help. Ibuprofen did relieve pain but not swelling.  By week 9, no relief from symptoms.  Podiatrist x-rayed affected areas and found no structural issues, but was concerned with Edema.  Administered steroid dosepack for 6 days.  Symptoms immediately abated.  No symptoms as of today.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1st Pfizer shot beginning of April went fine. Only a sore arm. 2nd shot this past Saturday was a different story. I got the shot around 3:30 and felt great until about 7. My arm started getting very sore. It got better a little later in the day.  Next morning I felt pretty fatigued but nothing I haven?t felt before. Sore arm was still there. Pretty manageable. Had to pick up groceries and that was a mistake. Had to take deep breaths and my knees were in a lot of pain as I got out of the car and walked through the store (I injured them years ago and now have Baker's cysts). Wife brought me home and I had rigors on the ride back.  I got home around 11:45 or so and I put on a blanket. I felt so hot I started to get a little bit delusional and very sad/started getting teary. Took off blanket and couldn?t get off the couch or walk without help. Knees now felt like about to fall apart. Wife takes temp shows 107, makes ice bath, I get in and it goes down to 105 a few minutes later. Temp went down to 103 over the next 15-20 minutes and stayed there. Got out with her help and still couldn?t stand up or walk without help.  Sat upright in bed rest of the day. Fever ranged from 98-103, mostly 101-103. Took a very cold shower later in the day but temp still stayed in the same range. All other symptoms mentions else stayed the same. I also now had no appetite and felt nauseous. Stomach felt rock hard, and I didn?t feel too with it. Finally fell asleep later at night and woke up feeling way better but still awful. Monday and Tuesday I had to take off work I felt so fatigued. Both of those days I had no fever, it went away from Sunday night into Monday. I can walk by myself now and just feel a little fatigued today. I have my appetite back now and am back to work.  I should mention that I took Tylenol which didn?t help. Ibuprofen I took later in the day and that might have helped a little. Took Benadryl later and that helped with sleep.

While receiving the vaccine I felt pain and burning.  That subsided after waiting the 15 minutes for monitoring.  When I arrived home my arm was sore, tight, and felt swollen.  I wasn't able to sleep on that side, I wasn't able to lift normal everyday items and I felt shooting pains as if I was getting injected again.  I treated myself with Aleeve and iced my arm (20 mins about 3x a day) for 3 days.  Symptoms still persisted.  At my second dose my experience was very different from the first however, the pain from the first one still remained.  I inquired if I should still feel this pain and I was told to expect soreness.  At the urge of my family and coworkers I went to my doctor on 5/4 and he informed me that I have shoulder bursitis due to the poor administration of the vaccine.  The person who gave it to me either went in the wrong spot, or went too deep.  I am being treated with Methylprednisolone tablets (4mg 21 tabs) currently.  My doctor said that if this doesn't work I would have to see an ortho and possibly need to get cortisone injections.  There is no way to tell if this will heal or if I will have to live with this for the rest of my life.  Poorly skilled administration of this vaccine so far has changed my life...and not for the better.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Vaccine administration error.  Event: Patient had 2nd Pfizer dose today (on 5/5/2021). Vaccine syringe malfunctioned during administration. Some vaccine leaked out around syringe during injection, and more vaccine leaked out of the arm after the needle was withdrawn. Vaccine administrator noted that some vaccine was visible remaining in the syringe after it was withdrawn. Administrator estimates that more than half of the 0.3mL dose leaked out of the patient, but is unsure on quantifying the amount.  Pt contact information was collected, and she left the facility before CDC guidelines specific to this issue were reviewed.   Treatment: After reviewing CDC guidelines specific to this issue regarding how much vaccine was administered after some leaked out, I spoke to pt over phone (at about 11:45 on 5/5/2021), explaining the CDC guideline to return for additional dose in opposite arm today, since it is estimated that less than half of dose remained in patient's arm during administration earlier today. Pt stated she would like to think about it, review guidelines herself, and consult her mother who is in the healthcare field before making decision. I emailed the link and screenshot about the CDC guidelines to the patient. Patient states that she would "probably" come back in as walk-in for repeat dose today or tomorrow.  I informed the patient of our hours for walk-ins, and that the CDC recommendation is to receive another dose today.  Outcome: patient was counseled that guideline recommendation was to return immediately for repeat dose of Pfizer in the opposite arm. As of time of this writing (12:50pm on 5/5/20201, patient has not returned to the facility for a repeat dose. She was provided with my contact information to address any questions or concerns about returning for a repeat dose. Health director was also notified of this incident and agreed with recommendation per CDC guideline for the patient to return today for repeat dose.

On 3/4/21, I was informed that I was pregnant with my 4th child. On 4/12/21, I was scheduled for my 1st dose of the Moderna as well as having a first trimester NCIT testing being done. At that exam, my provider was able to find a fetal heart rate (177), he was dated to be approximately 12 weeks and 6 days, and there were no concerns at that time regarding physical abnormalities or brain deformities. Additionally, I was sent out for bloodwork to rule out Trisomies and determined gender of the baby. The results of that lab work came back as negative and we were expecting our first son October 19, 2021. However, yesterday, 5/4/21, I attended my monthly prenatal appointment and the provider informed me that she could not find a heartbeat. She used a doppler scanner and then the in office ultrasound machine; neither of which detected a heartbeat. I was sent out to Radiology for a formal scan to refute or affirm the findings. Sadly, the results came back that I had lost my child. There was no heartbeat found and the results showed that my child stopped growing and remained 12 weeks in size. I am scheduled to have my pregnancy evacuated Friday, 5/7/21 at 1040a. While I am aware that miscarriage in 1 in 4 women, I cannot in good faith say that the vaccine may have contributed to my pregnancy loss. The only change in my routine was the addition of the vaccine. I am hopeful that this pain will not be felt by others and can be researched further to ensure fertility loss or future pregnancy loss isnt a norm following this vaccine.   Additionally, I have had 3 full term, healthy pregnancies prior to this miscarriage. None of these pregnancies had complications and the children were birthed without issue.

March 2 - second Moderna   March 3 - spontaneous bruising appears   March 4 - visit with primary care doctor, blood work shows significant drop in platelets   March 9 - first visit with oncologist/haematologist & hospitalized   March 9-19 - hospitalized for tests,  treatment to increase platelets, & many blood panels.  No official diagnosis, treat as  ITP.   Follow up visits with oncologist/haematologist to keep an eye on platelets as they increase.   March 30-Apr 4 - ER visit due to swelling of ankles, feet, and left arm. Tests show superficial blood clot, fluid on lungs, and pneumonia. Oncologist said that "we have no official diagnosis", that she's being treated for ITP.   April 6-14 - follow up visit to oncologist/haematologist show elevated kidney enzymes, then later liver enzymes,  low sodium.   April 14 - decision to move to short term rehab for regular PT and OT. Continued swelling (fluid in third spaces.)   April 21 - visit to cardiologist to perform cardioversion, successful (during first week of hospital stay, heart rhythm med had to stop).   April 23 - facility nurse discovered significantly low Hemoglobin and a blood transfusion was ordered.    April 24 - returned to short term rehab facility.   April 25 - discovered my mother on O2 and state of health was different,  extremely weak and not moving, arm hurting badly. I insisted that her oncologist is contacted. Transported to ER. Discovered her blood work abnormal. After stabilizing her, rushed to the hospital ICU.   April 26 -  Discussed with her ICU doctor the history of what you have read above. He explained that the covid-19 vaccination has a tendency to affect three proteins specifically that clot and thin blood. I begged him to "get it out of her system." Her bleeding was significant and platelets dropped, again. Still has her mental facilities. Responding well to aggressive treatment: albumin transfusion,  plateletpheresis, and CRRT. Pleural catheter to remove fluid from the lungs. Mention of Sepsis.   April 27 - Lifted her head up today, opened her eyes, making doctors very happy.  Her cardiologist and the ICU doctor both said they were "confused" and everything happening to my mom was "a mystery." Though going in to the evening, her nurse expressed to me that she's worried. The ICU oncologist called me at home in the evening.  He asked me if she had been having a fever on a regular basis. He said he thought it could be TTP or a rare disease called HTH, but both results wouldn't be back for one week. He planned to consult with a doctor.  He explained to me that the blood was attacking itself and "confused,"  and that her organs were shutting down. He indicated that the blood work wasn't indicating significant infection. He referenced how the vaccination has made her auto immune system "go crazy."   April 28 -  I get a call very early from the nurse that she has been fighting with my mother's blood pressure all night, trying to keep it elevated. She told me to come to the hospital, because she had taken a turn for the worse. I arrive to find my mother's eyes wide open, breathing shallow, and blood pressure steady, but drops without assistance from medication. She continues to have her mental facilities. She passed away, organs shutting down, and blood pressure dropped.
LAB_DATA: Can provide at a later date.
OTHER_MEDS: Rx: blood pressure, blood thinner, heart rhythm, cholesterol

SYMPTOM_TEXT: INITIALLY presented to ER 5/2 with generalized fatigues,body aches,and subjective fevers after receiving his 2nd dose of Pfizer Vaccine against CoVID-19 on 4/28/21. Patient reports dizzy spells over the past few days with shortness of breath and then last evening developed a diffuse rash over his chest and extremities associated with itching and burning sensation on 5/1 evening. He denies any nausea,vomiting,abdominal pain,diarrhea.No chest pain or cough.Denies headaches.Denies h/o of prior allergic reaction/concerns to the first dose of the vaccine or any other vaccine.Denies any new exposure other than as stated the 2nd dose of the covid vaccine. Treated with IV steroids, IV Pepcid, and IV Benadryl with improvement. Upon discharge, directed to continue Prednsione 40mg daily for three more days for a total of five days of steroids, and follow-up with PCP. SUBSEQUENTLY, returned to ER  acute onset of decreased visual acuity, diffuse arthralgias, joint pain, myalgias, lightheadedness, palpitations, vertigo, muscle spasms, and difficulty moving both upper extremities. This was accompanied by sharp, 10 out of 10, nonradiating, diffuse anterior chest pressure. Nothing made this better or worse. The patient was driving at that time, and was unable to control his arms, which resulted in his vehicle leaving the roadway.  He was able to bring the vehicle to a stop before crashing. Since then, his symptoms have gradually improved, although they have not completely resolved. The characteristics are identical to the events that led to his previous admission.
LAB_DATA: EKG, CBC, comprehensive metabolic panel, coagulation studies, magnesium, phosphorus, and TSH were near normal. First high sensitivity troponin was less than 6.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the morning of 3/2/2021 I was 27 weeks pregnant and had to complete my glucose screening exam. I drank the entire bottle of glucose and had my blood drawn at 9AM. Around 2pm that same day I had intense pain in my upper right stomach. It lasted for about 2 hours, subsided, and then happened again around 8pm. Once the 2nd round of pain came on, I checked myself into Labor and Delivery to make sure everything was okay with the baby. They ran many tests and could not find an issue. They made me leave without resolving anything. The following day I called my doctor about what happened and she scheduled me to have an ultrasound looking at my gallbladder. The following week we found that I had gallstones so I met with a surgeon and he suggested I have surgery to get my gallbladder removed. I cannot do this until after I give birth. I was out of work for 5 days because of the pain. When talking to my doctor, she thinks the trigger of the gallbladder attack was the glucose drink and not the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: Ultrasound on gallbladder - 3/5/2021 Results of gallstones on 3/8/2021

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient had second dose of Pfizer vaccine in morning. That afternoon began complaining of abdominal pain with subsequent vomiting (x2) and possible diarrhea. Patient could not sleep that evening . Awoke next morning with continued abdominal pain throughout the day and ultimately was found unresponsive in bed. Transported to hospital where he was pronounced dead. Subsequently autopsy was performed which revealed significant pre-existing hypertensive and atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease with evidence of acute myocardial infarction. There is no clear evidence that this is related to the vaccination, however it is being reported due to potential public health interest and temporal proximity to vaccination.
LAB_DATA: Autopsy was performed on April 2nd. No evidence of anaphylaxis/airway edema was found. No evidence of thrombi.  Autopsy confirmed significant pre-existing cardiac disease and histologic exam confirmed acute myocardial infarction.  Toxicology was non-contributory.  COVID-19 testing performed at the hospital was negative.
OTHER_MEDS: Aspirin, lisinopril, crestor, androgel, ibuprofen prn
HISTORY: Hypertensive and atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease, heart failure, status post remote quadruple CABG and endovascular coronary artery stent placement

Patient here at clinic today for her 2nd covid vaccine.  She denies having previous vaccine reaction.  She arrived in Covid Vaccine observation room after having receiving her 2nd dose of Pfizer Vaccine ER6206 at 1501.  She walked in with her father and was sitting for her 15 minutes.    She had been in the room about 10 minutes when she became diaphoretic.  Went to check on her and sent administrative help to find RN.   At her side she denied having any numbness, tingling or swelling  in her mouth at current time.   Said that she felt like her heart was racing.  And started shaking her right arm and leg at that time  and was not able to control movement. She told me she does not have any drug allergies. I put blood pressure cuff and pulse ox on her. RN in room.  BP at 1520 159/105 pulse 102 respirations 20, O2 100%.   RN sent me to get a provider.  She gave her Benadryl 25 mg and Pepcid 40 mg orally with water.  Her father had to hold the cup and give her the medicine.  She swallowed without difficulty.     MD in room at her side asking questions.  Admin person went to get patients mother.  RN on the phone with 911.     1525 bp 149/100, pulse 106, respirations 32 and O2 100%.   Father and mother stated she had 2 grand mal seizures at the ages of 5 & 7.  She does not take any medication for seizures currently.  And they told MD that she is under currently neurology care of a right hemisphere brain tumor.     Upon assessment she told MD that the feeling on right to left side was different.  She stated she was becoming numb completely on right side from face to her foot.  She started slurring her speech.  She was unable to squeeze with her right hand.   1532 bp 154/106, pulse 92, respirations 30 and O2 99%.  MD, RN and myself at her side with parents.   She said she did not want to go to the hospital but MD said she wanted her to go to be and examined and monitored.  Parents agreed.   Paramedics arrived at 1534.     MD gave them overview of what had been going on and they took over her care at 1536.  They did quick assessment and with slurred speech and not being able to hold right leg or arm up they decided to load her onto the stretcher.  RN and I helped them move her to the stretcher and secure her in.  They left with her at 1545 and said they were taking her to hospital.

CXR - normal, CTA Head perfusion with contrast and CTA head and neck with contrast - Negative, CT Head WO contrast negative, Had neurology evaluation while in ER. She was diagnosed with Hemiplegic Migraine without status migrainosus, not intractable.  ED note: Signed (Electronic Signature): 4/1/2021 5:15 PM  Signed By: MD     ED COURSE & MEDICAL DECISION MAKING   Pertinent Labs & Imaging studies reviewed. (See chart for details)   Labs: Laboratory studies are essentially unremarkable.    4:17 PM: Patient initially assessed.    4:20 PM: I consulted neurology.    5:05 PM: Patient reevaluated and updated after neurology evaluation and head CT. She endorses right-sided throbbing head pain and increased strength in her right side. Her mother was on the phone during this evaluation. The patient's father was updated, as he walked into the room during the evaluation.    5:12 PM: Radiologist confirming CT scans are negative.    10:17 PM: Patient reassessed and updated. We discussed plans for discharge and she is in agreement.    Patient is a 20 y.o. female with a history of pituitary adenoma and migraines who presents with right sided weakness and blurred vision after receiving her second COVID-19 vaccine. On initial exam patient's vital signs are stable. Patient's physical exam was notable for mild weakness to right side of face with forehead preserved and left extremity strength 5/5. She is alert and oriented x3. The patient has right extremity strength 3/5 in arm and leg and her light touches are in tact, but subjectively abnormal on the right. Clinical considerations include, but are not limited to, stroke, CVA, atypical migraine, medication side effect, brain mass, aneurysm, ICH, increased ICP, and seizure disorder.    On arrival the patient did have clear right-sided weakness concerning for acute stroke, therefore I ordered labs, a chest x-ray, a head and neck CTA, a head CT, and a brain MRI. I gave 324mg ASA, Benadryl, and compazine. A chest x-ray reveals no acute abnormality. A head CTA reveals no CTP evidence of core infarction or ischemic penumbra. A head CT reveals no acute intracranial abnormalities. A CTA of the head and neck is negative. The patient was seen by our neurology team who felt the presentation was consistent with a complex migraine.  The patient did develop a headache during her ER course.  Because of the concern for complex migraine patient did receive Benadryl and Compazine and an MRI was ordered.  A MRI shows no evidence of acute intracranial abnormality. EKG reveals normal sinus rhythm.   The MRI showed no acute abnormality, the patient states her headache is better and her symptoms have resolved.  This indicates there is no evidence for acute stroke, and is likely complex migraine.  Given the patient's marked improvement she is safe for discharge to home.  She does have a neurology specialist, I will refer her back to that specialist.   FINAL IMPRESSION   1. Hemiplegic migraine without status migrainosus, not intractable      DISPOSITION Discharged to home. The patient was asked to return to the emergency department for worsening illness or if needed.  The following instructions were provided: Follow-up with your neurologist within a week.    FOLLOW UP REFERRAL:   Schedule an appointment as soon as possible for a visit in 1 week

Patient is a 32-year-old female new patient 5 months post partum & currently breastfeeding, with seasonal and perennial allergic rhinitis and history of childhood asthma, referred by the emergency department to discuss anaphylaxis like reaction to the Johnson Johnson COVID-19 vaccination on 4/28/21.  She received her vaccine around 2:00 p.m. She began developing itchiness in her palms/soles of feet and scalp that quickly developed into a a welt like rash about 3-1/2 hours after receiving the vaccine while on a walk with her husband; this was shortly followed by facial swelling over her right eye.  They made it home and she got in a cold shower to cool down, became dizzy, started seeing spots and had difficulty breathing. Her husband called EMS and she was hypotensive when they arrived.  She was given 2 doses of epinephrine (0.2 mg each per ED note) and a dose of Benadryl which helped. Shortly after the 2nd dose, she began having difficulty swallowing, maintaining the ability to breathe through her nose. She was given a 3rd dose of epinephrine and transferred to the ED; during transport an IV was started with an epinephrine drip. She was seen at Emergency Department; she was given IV fluids, solu medrol, tryptase level and had a normal EKG.  She was discharged with an epi pen prescription. Tryptase is still pending at the time of her visit. She started a new prenatal vitamin at 11 am 4/28/21. Otherwise, she reports no new foods, medications or topical products. She did eat before going on a walk, pepper jack cheese, wheat thins, and black bean hummus. She is pretty sure she was not stung by a bee prior to onset of symptoms yesterday.   Interestingly she reports recent urticarial episodes that occurred in February of 2021. These occurred when she was visiting her in-laws and occurred in the middle of the night, 2 nights in a row during the middle of her visit.  She has never had hives previously.  She reports no family history of hives or anaphylaxis.  She reports no use of new topical products or medications.

Patient is a 37 yo female new patient referred by the ED for allergy consult on delayed urticarial/angioedema 2 days following the initial dose of Pfizer Covid19 vaccination.   Timeline:  4/19/21 Received her first Pfizer immunization at clinic.   4/21/21: She woke up with a systemic itchy rash. Worst in flexural regions like the folds of her groin, elbows, knees and where her bra meets her skin. The hives didn't stay fixed and didn't respond to benadryl. She also was experiencing joint pain in her hands and ankles.   4/23/21: Increased benadryl dose to 50 milligram Q4 hours which initially helped but then the hives returned.   4/27/21: Seen at a local urgent care and was prescribed a medrol dosepak. She didn't fill this immediately given pharmacy wait time.   4/28/21: Woke up with upper lip swelling. Went back to urgent care and was given epinephrine which didn't help. She was referred to the ED where she was given an IV, IV benadryl and more epinephrine. Tryptase was not obtained. At no time did she have dizziness, throat swelling, or difficulty breathing. Her lip swelling resolved and she was discharged home. Her blood pressure and respiratory exam in the ED were normal.   She continues to have itching and rare hives.   She is currently on day 3 of the medrol dosepak and is taking benadryl 50 mg. Q6H    She denies a history of medication/vaccine allergies/reactions.   She had recent IVF retrieval on 3/29 and is currently taking birth control pills for ovarian suppression.

Pfizer COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  Pfizer Dose 1 3/18/21 (EN6207) Pfizer Dose 2 4/8/21 (EW0161) COVID Positive 4/23/21  4/22/21: Presnted to ED. The patient presents with Nausea and vomiting. A 73 year old female with a history of UTI and DM was brought to the ED today due to having nausea and vomiting for the past couple of days. She was administered Zofran by EMS; they checked her BS which was 171. The patient states she has been sick since the eighth of this month, and has had diarrhea, dysuria, and  arm pain. She reports not taking her insulin since February due to her insurance no longer covering her. .  The onset was 3  days ago.  The course/duration of symptoms is constant.  The character of symptoms is unknown.  The degree at present is moderate.  The exacerbating factor is none.  The relieving factor is none.  Risk factors consist of diabetes mellitus. Therapy today: emergency medical services.  Associated symptoms: diarrhea.  4/30/21: A 73-year-old female, history of hypertension, diabetes mellitus type 2 with chronic kidney disease, adrenal insufficiency from renal cell carcinoma and adrenalectomy, and nonalcoholic steatohepatitis with portal hypertension, esophageal varices, has had nausea and vomiting for several days.  She did receive her second COVID-19 vaccination on April 8, and has had ongoing symptoms since that time, much worse in the 3 days prior to admission. An initial COVID screen was negative, but rechecking the PCR COVID test was positive.  Initially, she did not require any oxygen, but did require 2 L nasal cannula at night on the second night, at which time remdesivir and convalescent plasma were administered.  She was also given dexamethasone, but had marked rise in her blood sugar to greater than 400. The dexamethasone was tapered and stopped.  Glucose regulated with insulin.  The patient initially had severe anorexia, poor oral intake, but this slowly improved.  CT scan of the abdomen and pelvis has shown the small nodular liver consistent with cirrhosis and portal hypertension.  There is some ascites and mild pleural effusions.  The patient had been receiving some IV fluids, and we would discontinue the Lasix because of low blood pressure.  There was no other obvious explanation for her poor oral intake or abdominal pain. The patient had IV access problems and eventually, despite the PICC line and midlines being attempted, we were unable to complete a successful IV to finish her CAP antibiotics or the remdesivir. The patient seemed to be doing better, oxygen is 98% on room air, blood pressure 98/63 and 116/60.  We are holding the Lasix, potassium, and spironolactone.  The glucose has been running at 213, 154, and 202.  BUN at 35, creatinine 1.4.  WBC 11,700 and hemoglobin 11.5. The patient was seen on the day of discharge at 1100 hours, doing quite well, and will be discharged home with her family.  We have offered visiting nurses, but she feels that the family is there 24 hours a day.  She does not need any visiting nurses.  We have made some changes to her medications, and she will need to follow up with her primary doctor in the next week to see whether we need to restart Lasix, potassium, and spironolactone. DISCHARGE MEDICATIONS:  Will be hydrocortisone 15 mg a.m., 5 mg evening, venlafaxine 37.5 daily, venlafaxine 150 mg at bedtime, rifaximin 550 mg b.i.d., Bactrim DS 1 daily, multivitamins daily, insulin glargine 35 units at bedtime, atorvastatin 20 mg daily, NovoLog 20 units before meals. SYMPTOM_TEXT: The client received the COVID vaccine (Pfizer dose 1, lot # EW0167, expiration date 5/6/2021) at 1430. At 1500, she reported a "pinching" sensation in her left chest, which didn't get worse or better upon inspiration or expiration. The pinching sensation was intermittent and didn't radiate. RN and EMT responded at this time. She denied any shortness of breath or changes in vision, and had no visible flushing, diaphoresis, or swelling. The client was sitting in her chair in the observation area, in no apparent distress. At 1505, the client's vital signs were as follows: blood pressure 144/100, heart rate 82, respiratory rate 12, and O2 96%. Lung sounds were clear to auscultation bilaterally. The client stated her blood pressure is "usually high" but wasn't sure of her exact baseline. The client stated that she hadn't eaten or drank anything yet that day. She was offered water at that time, which she accepted. The client stated she has a history of fibromyalgia, migraines, and obesity, and she takes duloxetine, gabapentin, and vitamins. She has allergies to keflex and ben-gay. The client was alert and oriented. She denied any need to lie down and stated her symptoms were improving. At 1510, the client's vital signs were as follows: blood pressure 140/98, heart rate 78, respiratory rate 12, and O2 98%. She was offered benadryl, which she declined. The client stated that her symptoms had resolved at that time and she wanted to go home. Client advised of recommended 30 minute wait time and educated regarding emergency management, AMR activation, v-safe, and primary care follow up. The client stood up without any dizziness and ambulated to her car with a steady gait, where she was driven home by her husband.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Event: In February, 2018 I received (in my right shoulder); my 5th anthrax shot.  The initial part of the day was typical (burning, soreness?) however, when I was traveling home my arm developed a fever. Around the injection site I developed severe swelling to the point that it looked like I had a golf ball under my skin. My arm was hot to the touch, itchy and painful. I had a large red area on my upper arm maybe the size of a softball. It remained swollen for more than 12 hours. I applied a cool rag to help with the fever. I assumed that this was not normal and I contacted the flight doc. He mentioned that it was a possible side effect and that I should continue to monitor without great concern. After about a week the area seemed to be back to normal but had a tightness to the skin. Although it was not sudden my right pinky was numb for some time and my right shoulder joint remained achy.  Fast forward 3 months later: Now at the location my arm randomly swelled up at the injection sight and became feverish again. I went and reported to the flight doc and he said again it?s normal to have reactions to the shot although it seemed odd that it was so long ago. After about 6-7 hours the sight subsided. I thought it was a one-time event.  Fast forward another 3-4 months, now post. I was at on leave and the sight became inflamed again. Although I have not been able to retrieve the picture; I remember taking a picture and sending it to the flight doc. He said it probably was not the shot but something else that I was having a reaction to.  Follow on: Pretty much 3-4 months sometimes a little longer my right shoulder will randomly get raised and itch. To the best of my knowledge I have not found any ?triggers?. The last time it happened it was a very small area maybe the size of a flat pea and the skin around the area got blotchy red and itched. Almost like when bitten by a bug. The duration was only for a matter of an hour or so.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient, received the 2nd dose of the Pfizer COVID vaccine Lot # EW0167, Expiring 05/04/21 at 1105. EMTs noticed a client on the floor at about 1110 and rushed over to see what was going on. EMT went to tell lead nurse of the incident. The client was on the floor lying down when the EMTs and lead nurse went over to respond. Per report from one of the patients sitting next to patient in the observation area, Patient started leaning forward in her chair, started falling over, and the patient caught her before she could hit her head and slowly helped her to a lying position on the floor. Patient woke up on the floor at about 1111 and did not remember fainting. Vitals were taken at that time, P: 88, SpO2: 100, and BP: 138/96. The client upon waking up was A/O x 4 and stated that she "felt fine." She takes no medications, has no allergies, and has no medical history. The client ate some food in her car right before the appointment and explained that she had 4 shots of espresso in the morning. At about 1115 the client was slowly assisted to a chair in the observation area and was given some water to drink. The client stated that she has fainted before while donating blood about 4 years ago but that this has never happened after a vaccine. Vitals were taken again at 1121, P: 85, SpO2: 99, and BP: 120/78. Vital signs were within normal limits and the client felt "like normal". At 1135 the client verbalized feeling good and ambulated out of the facility and was able to safely drive herself home.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got my second Moderna dose around noon on 5/4 (yesterday). By the time I went to bed that night, I was feeling some of the common and expected side effects: mild-moderate joint/muscle aches; chills; headache. I woke close to 1 am and got out of bed to go to the bathroom. As soon as I stood up, all of my muscles felt so weak I thought I would collapse. I felt all the blood rush to my head, which started spinning. Once I sat on the toilet, I felt like I was simultaneously going to vomit and pass out. I put my head between my legs. I remember coming to a short time later. I believe I briefly passed out. Still feeling my head swimming, I tried to make it back to bed, but I had to crawl to avoid passing out or vomiting. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 12:05pm on 5/5/21, Five minutes after receiving the vaccine, the patient fainted while in the waiting room.  We came out to assist and at that point the patient was already sitting up, but on the floor.  We were able to speak to him and gave him some water to drink.  We called 911, when we were aware he had fainted.  I was the pharmacist on duty, but not the one that vaccinated him.  So I stayed with him.  There was a moment when he took his sweater off saying he was hot, and I saw sweat bullets on his forehead.  So I got some paper towels for him and took his temperature, which read around 98 degrees.  A few seconds later he turned pale and fell over, hitting his head on one of the shelves.  I quickly got him off the shelf and held his head in my arms .  He opened his eyes and started talking and wanting to sit up, but we kept him laying down and continued to ask him questions to keep him alert.  He was able to answer the questions, knew where he was, who he was, who he was with .  The paramedics then arrived and he was taken out of the store on a stretcher.  We provided a copy of the report he filled out to the paramedics .
CHILLS, BODY ACHES, FATIGUE
